WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:03:59.068 --> 00:04:02.707
Holy Father. may I present General Helm.
Commander of the SS in Italy?

3
00:04:02.986 --> 00:04:06.425
Your Holiness.
I've come to pay you my respects...

4
00:04:07.784 --> 00:04:11.903
.. and to inform you officially
that the German army is in total control of Rome.

5
00:04:12.303 --> 00:04:15.741
In other words. General.
your forces have occupied our city.

6
00:04:16.021 --> 00:04:19.180
And I'm to convey
the Fuhrer's personal guarantee

7
00:04:19.380 --> 00:04:22.339
that Vatican neutrality
will continue to be respected.

8
00:04:22.738 --> 00:04:25.617
<i>In return. I would ask Your Holiness to confirm</i>

9
00:04:25.897 --> 00:04:29.536
in your communiques. German troops.
particularly the SS detachments.

10
00:04:29.816 --> 00:04:32.215
are behaving correctly and with restraint.

11
00:04:32.534 --> 00:04:36.733
<i>I shall be happy to report
that you have asked me to confirm that. General.</i>

12
00:04:43.170 --> 00:04:46.129
May I present Colonel Herbert Kappler?

13
00:04:47.289 --> 00:04:50.527
<i>ColoneI Kappler has been personally selected
by Reichsfuhrer Himmler</i>

14
00:04:50.927 --> 00:04:52.167
<i>as Head of Police in Rome.</i>

15
00:04:52.446 --> 00:04:57.444
<i>I am relieved to hear that the German police
consider it their duty to protect ordinary citizens.</i>

16
00:04:57.844 --> 00:05:01.643
My duty is to maintain order in the streets.
discourage resistance.

17
00:05:02.043 --> 00:05:04.162
and to round up escaped prisoners.

18
00:05:04.442 --> 00:05:06.441
<i>Prisoners?
- After Italy's capitulation.</i>

19
00:05:06.641 --> 00:05:09.520
many enemy prisoners of war
escaped from prison camps.

20
00:05:09.719 --> 00:05:11.639
which were left unguarded.

21
00:05:11.839 --> 00:05:15.477
And we have reason to believe
that large numbers are heading for Rome.

22
00:05:15.837 --> 00:05:19.595
Some may even be making for the Vatican...
to seek refuge.

23
00:05:19.875 --> 00:05:22.954
<i>These. of course. will be arrested
before they reach here. but.</i>

24
00:05:23.314 --> 00:05:27.832
in case of unfortunate incidents. I intend.
with your permission.

25
00:05:28.112 --> 00:05:31.950
to have a white line drawn across
the opening of St Peter's Square.

26
00:05:32.230 --> 00:05:36.349
<i>The line will show the exact start
of Vatican territory</i>

27
00:05:36.669 --> 00:05:39.148
and. at the same time.
make my men aware of it

28
00:05:39.427 --> 00:05:42.986
<i>and prevent any of them -
any armed German soldiers -</i>

29
00:05:43.346 --> 00:05:45.185
<i>from violating it.</i>

30
00:05:45.465 --> 00:05:48.144
I thank you for your consideration. Colonel.

31
00:05:48.344 --> 00:05:53.422
And I can only hope that our relations
between the Church and your armed forces

32
00:05:53.702 --> 00:05:57.660
will remain as reasonable.
Good day. gentlemen.

33
00:06:18.052 --> 00:06:22.370
It's certainly a relief. Holy Father.
They seem prepared to act reasonably.

34
00:06:26.768 --> 00:06:29.767
<i>He must have been very sure of my permission.</i>

35
00:06:30.127 --> 00:06:32.846
Kappler is the one to watch. of course.

36
00:06:33.126 --> 00:06:34.925
<i>with his white line.</i>

37
00:06:35.205 --> 00:06:38.004
<i>It is not meant merely to keep his men out.</i>

38
00:06:38.284 --> 00:06:42.042
<i>it is a reminder to us of our authority.
of how far we can go.</i>

39
00:07:24.025 --> 00:07:26.304
Come on. lad. come on.
Don't be afraid to hit me.

40
00:07:26.624 --> 00:07:28.903
Come on.

41
00:07:32.462 --> 00:07:34.861
<i>That's it.</i>

42
00:07:35.221 --> 00:07:37.620
<i>Sei bravo! Ancora. ancora!
Bene. bene.</i>

43
00:07:37.940 --> 00:07:39.179
Watch it. now.

44
00:07:39.459 --> 00:07:41.738
That's the boy.

45
00:07:44.337 --> 00:07:47.696
E vai. e vai ancora. ancora!
Cosi. cosi! Ancora. dai!

46
00:07:48.095 --> 00:07:50.974
Are you all right?
- Yeah. I'm all right.

47
00:07:52.214 --> 00:07:55.732
Now. you've a trick of leaning to the left
when you're going to hook.

48
00:07:56.132 --> 00:07:58.051
That's when you leave yourself open.

49
00:07:58.251 --> 00:08:00.650
Try to remember that.

50
00:08:10.886 --> 00:08:13.965
<i>But this is the Vatican.
Just let us speak with someone.</i>

51
00:08:14.365 --> 00:08:17.244
United States. Americano.

52
00:08:17.404 --> 00:08:19.243
English. Tommy.

53
00:08:19.523 --> 00:08:21.362
B-1 7.

54
00:08:21.642 --> 00:08:23.841
Crashed. Bomber. bomber. Savvy?

55
00:08:24.121 --> 00:08:26.440
<i>No. Via. via!</i>

56
00:08:26.720 --> 00:08:28.439
I thought they had to give us shelter.

57
00:08:28.719 --> 00:08:31.718
I thought they had to help anyone who asked.
- Bleedin' Eyeties.

58
00:08:31.878 --> 00:08:35.356
There's no need to go running away.
- You speak English?

59
00:08:35.636 --> 00:08:38.035
After a fashion. The name's O'Flaherty.

60
00:08:38.995 --> 00:08:40.634
You lads look terrible.

61
00:08:40.794 --> 00:08:44.273
<i>Could you do with a bite to eat
and a place to stay? Come on.</i>

62
00:08:46.552 --> 00:08:48.591
Well. I'd advise you to trust me

63
00:08:48.871 --> 00:08:51.630
or you'll end up in Regina Coeli prison
by nightfall.

64
00:08:53.829 --> 00:08:57.987
Now. come on. Follow me.
And don't be talking out loud in English.

65
00:09:08.623 --> 00:09:10.702
In you go. now. No-one's going to stop you.

66
00:09:11.022 --> 00:09:13.101
Third floor. room at the end of the passage.

67
00:09:13.421 --> 00:09:17.699
I've a bit of business to see to
and I'll join you as soon as I can. In you go.

68
00:09:19.339 --> 00:09:22.297
Excuse me. but er... what is this place?

69
00:09:26.536 --> 00:09:28.935
No speaka da lingo.

70
00:09:29.494 --> 00:09:31.893
It's some kind of hostel. isn't it?

71
00:09:32.573 --> 00:09:36.132
It seems like it. but I'm not sure if it's...

72
00:09:37.371 --> 00:09:38.891
Isn't Hugh here?

73
00:09:39.011 --> 00:09:41.410
Hugh?
- Hugh O'Flaherty.

74
00:09:42.049 --> 00:09:44.448
How silly of me. I can see he isn't.

75
00:09:46.288 --> 00:09:48.687
I'm sorry. I haven't introduced myself.

76
00:09:49.726 --> 00:09:53.365
I am Francesca. Francesca Lombardo.
And you?

77
00:09:53.685 --> 00:09:58.283
I'm Lieutenant Manning. US Air Corps. This is
Corporal Tate. British 6th Armoured Division.

78
00:09:58.563 --> 00:10:00.082
When were you captured?

79
00:10:00.282 --> 00:10:04.200
My name is Lieutenant Jack Manning.
my number is 0-7-6-4...

80
00:10:04.400 --> 00:10:07.839
If you're only going to repeat your name.
rank and number. Lieutenant.

81
00:10:08.239 --> 00:10:10.838
the conversation
is going to be terribly one-sided.

82
00:10:13.317 --> 00:10:16.276
I was picked up in North Africa. miss.
when Tobruk fell.

83
00:10:16.675 --> 00:10:19.074
The lieutenant was shot down a few weeks ago.

84
00:10:20.594 --> 00:10:24.912
We were in a camp south of here. and yesterday
the Germans shoved us all into cattle trucks.

85
00:10:25.392 --> 00:10:29.230
We didn't fancy a trip to the Third Reich
so we jumped off and stole some clothes.

86
00:10:29.510 --> 00:10:30.870
I see.

87
00:10:31.150 --> 00:10:34.588
And er... what about you? Are you Italian?

88
00:10:34.868 --> 00:10:38.147
My late husband was Italian.
but I am from Malta.

89
00:10:39.306 --> 00:10:41.225
So you could say I was British.

90
00:10:41.425 --> 00:10:42.825
Well. well.

91
00:10:43.145 --> 00:10:46.303
And now you just sort of... live here
with Mr O'Flaherty.

92
00:10:46.583 --> 00:10:48.982
I don't actually live here...

93
00:10:49.182 --> 00:10:51.101
but I call in quite often.

94
00:10:51.381 --> 00:10:53.101
Where is he now?

95
00:10:53.381 --> 00:10:55.100
In his office. I expect.

96
00:10:55.300 --> 00:10:57.899
He's kept pretty busy.

97
00:11:00.578 --> 00:11:02.977
Blimey.

98
00:11:03.736 --> 00:11:06.055
You've had something to eat. have you? Good.

99
00:11:06.335 --> 00:11:08.614
And you've met Mrs Lombardo.

100
00:11:09.894 --> 00:11:12.573
Well now. what are you doing in Rome?

101
00:11:12.773 --> 00:11:14.852
The Vatican's neutral. right. sir?

102
00:11:15.132 --> 00:11:18.610
That's what the chaps always said.
"If you get stuck. make for the Vatican. "

103
00:11:18.890 --> 00:11:23.568
The trouble was so many people were given
sanctuary during the early days of the war

104
00:11:23.888 --> 00:11:27.807
the Vatican was about to burst at the seams.
so the gates had to be shut.

105
00:11:28.206 --> 00:11:29.646
What about this place?

106
00:11:29.806 --> 00:11:33.564
This is a religious hostel on Vatican territory.
safe enough. for the moment.

107
00:11:33.844 --> 00:11:36.803
Excuse me. sir. Are you some kind of bishop?

108
00:11:37.123 --> 00:11:40.561
Not nearly that exalted. just a monsignor.

109
00:11:40.761 --> 00:11:42.561
Come in.

110
00:11:42.841 --> 00:11:45.240
<i>Ah. Vittorio.</i>

111
00:11:45.440 --> 00:11:48.038
I've got what you wanted.
- That's the boy.

112
00:11:48.318 --> 00:11:50.517
This is my old pal Father Vittorio.

113
00:11:50.797 --> 00:11:52.637
Good afternoon. gentlemen.

114
00:11:52.837 --> 00:11:55.236
Ah. that's just the ticket.

115
00:11:55.795 --> 00:11:58.274
Some decent clothes. spruce you up a bit.

116
00:11:58.474 --> 00:12:02.872
Lieutenant Manning can wear one of mine.
- Where are you going to put them?

117
00:12:03.272 --> 00:12:06.071
San Sepolcro?
- That's where I put that last lot.

118
00:12:06.231 --> 00:12:09.310
<i>I've got the RAF bunch at Via Mazzini.</i>

119
00:12:09.590 --> 00:12:12.948
<i>I think we'll try the Ursuline Convent.
- There's no more room at the convent.</i>

120
00:12:13.228 --> 00:12:15.068
but I know where they can go.

121
00:12:15.347 --> 00:12:16.787
Home with me.

122
00:12:17.067 --> 00:12:18.906
Oh. no. you don't.

123
00:12:19.106 --> 00:12:20.905
That's altogether too risky.

124
00:12:21.185 --> 00:12:23.224
I'm not even going to consider it.

125
00:12:23.504 --> 00:12:26.583
You're going to have to...
because I want to help.

126
00:12:26.863 --> 00:12:29.342
And this time you're not going to put me off.

127
00:12:32.021 --> 00:12:33.860
So that's the way it is. is it?

128
00:12:34.140 --> 00:12:36.459
It is.

129
00:12:37.698 --> 00:12:39.418
Well. all right.

130
00:12:39.698 --> 00:12:42.017
Only for a couple of days.

131
00:12:42.576 --> 00:12:45.375
My old tweed golf jacket. That'll do you fine.

132
00:12:45.655 --> 00:12:47.774
It's a good thing you're pro-British. Father.

133
00:12:48.054 --> 00:12:52.532
Holy Mother. that's the first time
I've ever been accused of that.

134
00:13:03.848 --> 00:13:05.767
Oh. Herbert...

135
00:13:06.047 --> 00:13:08.446
it's... it's unbelievable.

136
00:13:08.646 --> 00:13:10.965
Yes. Unbelievable as it is. it's real.

137
00:13:11.245 --> 00:13:13.244
You know something. Minna?

138
00:13:13.564 --> 00:13:15.843
It's mine.

139
00:13:16.883 --> 00:13:19.681
And if you're nice to me. I'll give it to you.
- Pappi. Pappi!

140
00:13:19.881 --> 00:13:21.321
Ah!

141
00:13:21.601 --> 00:13:25.439
Careful. Pappi. you'll mess my hair.
- You're your mother's daughter. Liesel.

142
00:13:25.639 --> 00:13:27.078
Whoop-pa.
- Look. look!

143
00:13:27.238 --> 00:13:29.078
I'll tell you something. children.

144
00:13:29.278 --> 00:13:32.036
When I was little more than a boy
I came here to this city.

145
00:13:32.316 --> 00:13:34.156
I walked everywhere.

146
00:13:34.435 --> 00:13:37.234
I saw every street and square.

147
00:13:37.514 --> 00:13:39.913
And I fell in love...

148
00:13:40.473 --> 00:13:41.912
.. with Rome.

149
00:13:42.112 --> 00:13:43.552
<i>It's true.</i>

150
00:13:43.752 --> 00:13:49.110
And I always promised myself that one day
I would come back to claim her.

151
00:13:49.509 --> 00:13:50.949
What's that. Pappi?

152
00:13:51.109 --> 00:13:53.148
<i>That's the Victor EmmanueI Monument.</i>

153
00:13:53.428 --> 00:13:55.827
It looks like a wedding cake. huh?

154
00:13:56.107 --> 00:13:57.946
And there. Liesel.

155
00:13:58.226 --> 00:14:00.025
there is the Campidoglio.

156
00:14:00.225 --> 00:14:02.144
where the Temple of Jupiter stood.

157
00:14:02.424 --> 00:14:05.503
All the Roman emperors
used to celebrate their triumphs in war.

158
00:14:05.783 --> 00:14:07.222
What's that. Pappi?

159
00:14:07.502 --> 00:14:09.261
<i>St Peter's. at the Vatican.</i>

160
00:14:09.421 --> 00:14:11.461
<i>Where's the Colosseum?</i>

161
00:14:11.740 --> 00:14:14.339
You can't see it from here.
- Can we go there. Pappi?

162
00:14:14.699 --> 00:14:16.538
Yes. I'll take you when I have time.

163
00:14:16.818 --> 00:14:20.177
I want to go now.
- I told you. I'll take you there soon.

164
00:14:20.457 --> 00:14:22.856
Maybe tomorrow.

165
00:14:23.256 --> 00:14:25.615
We can go anywhere we like.

166
00:14:27.054 --> 00:14:29.453
Rome is ours.

167
00:14:59.201 --> 00:15:01.600
<i>Scusi. dove si va per la Piazza Navona?</i>

168
00:15:05.719 --> 00:15:08.677
<i>Scusi. dove si va per la Piazza Navona?</i>

169
00:15:15.954 --> 00:15:18.353
<i>Per Piazza Navona. dove si scende?</i>

170
00:15:26.990 --> 00:15:31.028
<i>Scusi. dove si va per la Piazza Navona?
- La terza fermata. signora.</i>

171
00:15:31.308 --> 00:15:34.067
<i>Grazie.
- Prego.</i>

172
00:15:38.785 --> 00:15:41.184
Halt.

173
00:15:45.982 --> 00:15:48.381
Documenti. Documenti.

174
00:15:50.940 --> 00:15:52.780
<i>Andiamo. svegliati! Andiamo.</i>

175
00:15:53.059 --> 00:15:54.899
<i>E voi?</i>

176
00:15:55.059 --> 00:15:57.458
<i>Documento.</i>

177
00:15:57.937 --> 00:16:00.337
Un altro.

178
00:16:02.736 --> 00:16:05.135
Documenti.

179
00:16:09.733 --> 00:16:12.132
<i>E voi?</i>

180
00:16:12.532 --> 00:16:14.931
Documento.

181
00:16:15.290 --> 00:16:17.689
<i>Documento.</i>

182
00:16:23.167 --> 00:16:25.566
<i>Ancora.</i>

183
00:16:30.244 --> 00:16:32.643
Documento.

184
00:17:23.463 --> 00:17:25.862
This way. please.

185
00:17:41.696 --> 00:17:44.095
Good evening. Monsignor.
- Good evening. Emilia.

186
00:17:44.374 --> 00:17:48.293
You remember our friend Simon. don't you?
- Yes. you're the one who's at medical school.

187
00:17:48.693 --> 00:17:51.172
How's it all going?
- It was going well. Monsignor.

188
00:17:51.372 --> 00:17:53.291
till the Germans came.

189
00:17:53.451 --> 00:17:57.129
My family is Jewish.
They know what may happen.

190
00:17:57.489 --> 00:17:59.888
This is my elder daughter Guila.

191
00:18:01.128 --> 00:18:05.646
my other daughter Emilia
and our friend Simon Weiss.

192
00:18:05.926 --> 00:18:09.684
These gentlemen are Allied soldiers.
They're going to stay with us for a while.

193
00:18:09.844 --> 00:18:13.523
We're very grateful to you. Mrs Lombardo.
but we won't be here long.

194
00:18:13.803 --> 00:18:15.922
We'll rest. then we'll head for the Allied lines.

195
00:18:16.202 --> 00:18:20.800
There's not a chance. lad. The whole German
army's between you and your people in Salerno.

196
00:18:21.080 --> 00:18:23.878
<i>In a couple of days I'll have you moved
somewhere more permanent.</i>

197
00:18:24.038 --> 00:18:26.837
We'll see about that.
- Ah.

198
00:18:27.117 --> 00:18:29.516
Come on. let's get things ready.

199
00:18:30.396 --> 00:18:32.675
In the meantime. please don't worry.

200
00:18:32.875 --> 00:18:35.754
Things will be a bit crowded. but we'll manage.

201
00:18:36.114 --> 00:18:38.513
I'm sure we will.

202
00:18:40.912 --> 00:18:44.750
It'll be like a rest-cure
after what we've been through. ma'am.

203
00:18:45.030 --> 00:18:47.429
Don't get carried away. lads.

204
00:18:48.708 --> 00:18:51.068
This isn't all fun and games. you know.

205
00:18:52.347 --> 00:18:56.065
If there's any trouble. your duty is to get out fast.

206
00:18:56.265 --> 00:18:59.504
Don't tell anyone where you've been hiding.
whatever happens.

207
00:18:59.904 --> 00:19:02.303
If you're captured. you'll only be put in jail.

208
00:19:04.622 --> 00:19:06.981
Mrs Lombardo and her daughters will be shot.

209
00:19:23.095 --> 00:19:24.814
What is this?

210
00:19:25.134 --> 00:19:28.013
A report on known black market operators. sir.
- Yes. Next.

211
00:19:28.292 --> 00:19:31.051
A report on the water and electricity supplies.
- Next.

212
00:19:31.451 --> 00:19:33.730
A list of suspected members
of Resistance groups.

213
00:19:34.050 --> 00:19:36.729
They must be kept under surveillance. Hirsch.

214
00:19:36.929 --> 00:19:39.288
At the first sign of trouble. round them up.

215
00:19:39.608 --> 00:19:42.367
What is the latest on those escaped prisoners?

216
00:19:43.526 --> 00:19:46.765
A number have been picked up. sir. Er... 53.

217
00:19:46.965 --> 00:19:48.324
Only 53?

218
00:19:48.604 --> 00:19:51.203
Army intelligence
said hundreds were heading for Rome.

219
00:19:51.483 --> 00:19:53.762
They cannot be here yet.

220
00:19:54.442 --> 00:19:56.161
I don't accept that. Hirsch.

221
00:19:56.281 --> 00:19:59.160
They must be finding places to hide
before we can arrest them.

222
00:19:59.520 --> 00:20:02.399
Most of the men picked up. sir.
were heading for the Vatican.

223
00:20:02.599 --> 00:20:05.278
They seemed to think
they would be given shelter there.

224
00:20:05.477 --> 00:20:07.317
I see.
- Up to a few months ago

225
00:20:07.597 --> 00:20:11.995
a committee of the Holy Office
was in charge of welfare in the Italian camps.

226
00:20:12.395 --> 00:20:14.474
What is it. this Holy Office?

227
00:20:14.674 --> 00:20:17.273
It's the secret court of the Catholic Church. sir.

228
00:20:17.473 --> 00:20:19.872
It used to be known as the Inquisition.

229
00:20:20.911 --> 00:20:22.750
Indeed.

230
00:20:23.030 --> 00:20:27.429
Now it handles all cases of divorce. heresy.
challenges to the faith. and so on.

231
00:20:27.708 --> 00:20:29.548
And this committee?

232
00:20:29.828 --> 00:20:31.947
A welfare group set up by the Pope.

233
00:20:32.147 --> 00:20:33.946
But it was headed by...

234
00:20:34.226 --> 00:20:35.945
Cardinal Crespini.

235
00:20:36.265 --> 00:20:38.664
But it was largely run
by a man named O'Flaherty.

236
00:20:38.824 --> 00:20:40.943
O'Flaherty. What is he?
- A monsignor. sir.

237
00:20:41.143 --> 00:20:43.902
A high official in the Holy Office.
A sort of religious lawyer.

238
00:20:44.102 --> 00:20:46.141
What else?
- There is no more information.

239
00:20:46.301 --> 00:20:49.300
We could find out more about him.
his associates. people around him.

240
00:20:49.580 --> 00:20:51.979
Yes. well. don't spend too much time on it.

241
00:20:52.938 --> 00:20:56.857
Still. it might be useful. at least.
to know where he fits in...

242
00:20:58.096 --> 00:21:00.495
.. this Monsignor O'Flaherty.

243
00:21:09.412 --> 00:21:10.851
Coffee. Monsignor?

244
00:21:11.131 --> 00:21:14.130
Well. I wouldn't say no.
That smells like the real article.

245
00:21:14.410 --> 00:21:18.448
I believe it is. Mr West seems able
to maintain a regular supply...

246
00:21:18.728 --> 00:21:21.127
though I'm careful not to ask how.

247
00:21:23.886 --> 00:21:26.565
Well. now. Sir D'Arcy. let's get back to business.

248
00:21:26.765 --> 00:21:29.443
Ah. yes. some 40 Allied escapers. you say?

249
00:21:29.843 --> 00:21:32.722
They're mostly British.
A few Americans. some French.

250
00:21:33.002 --> 00:21:37.880
I've been hiding them out in various colleges.
monasteries. a couple of private homes.

251
00:21:38.280 --> 00:21:40.759
Well. that's very fine of you. A splendid effort.

252
00:21:41.039 --> 00:21:43.638
Well. the point is.
there are going to be a lot more.

253
00:21:43.918 --> 00:21:45.557
Are you sure of that?

254
00:21:45.837 --> 00:21:48.516
<i>Nothing could be more certain.
It's going to be a major problem.</i>

255
00:21:48.716 --> 00:21:51.235
They've got to be housed. fed and clothed.

256
00:21:52.274 --> 00:21:55.513
I've done all that I can on my own.
Now you'll have to take over.

257
00:21:55.913 --> 00:21:58.792
But I cannot possibly become involved.
Monsignor.

258
00:21:59.072 --> 00:22:01.551
I can't take any responsibility for it.

259
00:22:01.950 --> 00:22:04.070
What are you saying to me. man?

260
00:22:04.349 --> 00:22:06.748
In the name of God. you're the British minister.

261
00:22:07.028 --> 00:22:11.546
But my dear man. I've been a prisoner here
in the Vatican since the beginning of the war.

262
00:22:11.906 --> 00:22:15.385
This work of yours needs someone
who can move about.

263
00:22:15.665 --> 00:22:19.103
<i>You must understand that.
as Minister to the Holy See.</i>

264
00:22:19.383 --> 00:22:24.581
<i>my strictest duty is to do nothing which might
compromise the neutrality of the Vatican state</i>

265
00:22:24.941 --> 00:22:26.780
<i>or of His Holiness the Pope.</i>

266
00:22:26.980 --> 00:22:30.539
Though. naturally. this whole business
upsets me dreadfully.

267
00:22:32.898 --> 00:22:34.737
I've had enough.

268
00:22:35.017 --> 00:22:40.095
<i>Well. since most of them are British.
I naturally thought I should come here.</i>

269
00:22:40.495 --> 00:22:42.774
If you'll pardon me.

270
00:22:43.454 --> 00:22:45.653
I think I've taken up enough of your time.

271
00:22:45.973 --> 00:22:48.931
Well. it was kind of you to call
and fill me in on the problem.

272
00:22:49.211 --> 00:22:51.410
but. really. my butler - Mr West -

273
00:22:51.690 --> 00:22:54.409
he knows more about what's going on than I do.

274
00:22:58.687 --> 00:23:01.086
"Most kind of you. "

275
00:23:02.166 --> 00:23:04.645
"Not my concern. "

276
00:23:05.685 --> 00:23:08.084
"So dreadfully sorry. "

277
00:23:09.723 --> 00:23:12.122
Come in.

278
00:23:13.362 --> 00:23:14.801
<i>Mr West.</i>

279
00:23:15.001 --> 00:23:17.120
Sorry to interrupt you at your work. sir.

280
00:23:17.320 --> 00:23:19.239
You'd better be careful what you say.

281
00:23:19.519 --> 00:23:21.918
Yes. I didn't think you looked happy
when you left us. sir.

282
00:23:22.198 --> 00:23:25.916
Mm. Well. it may surprise you to learn
that I was born and raised in Ireland.

283
00:23:26.236 --> 00:23:29.195
<i>During the Troubles
some of my closest friends in college</i>

284
00:23:29.555 --> 00:23:32.554
were shot by the Black and Tans.

285
00:23:32.834 --> 00:23:35.233
So I have my own opinion of the English

286
00:23:35.513 --> 00:23:38.311
and it's just been beautifully confirmed.

287
00:23:38.471 --> 00:23:42.150
Yes. I understand we're not too popular
in certain parts of Ireland. sir.

288
00:23:42.510 --> 00:23:45.189
However.
the minister would like you to have this.

289
00:23:55.664 --> 00:23:57.943
- 60.000 lire.
- Sir D'Arcy's sorry. sir.

290
00:23:58.223 --> 00:23:59.783
It's all he can spare at the moment.

291
00:24:00.063 --> 00:24:02.342
It's for food and clothes and stuff
for the escapers.

292
00:24:02.662 --> 00:24:05.540
Oh. he's changed his tune. has he?
- Oh. Lord love you. sir!

293
00:24:07.939 --> 00:24:10.498
Which I'm sure he does.
No. he meant what he said.

294
00:24:10.698 --> 00:24:13.657
The Vatican's neutrality
is really most precarious.

295
00:24:13.977 --> 00:24:17.296
The minister has to be very careful.
but he's keen to assist you in any way he can.

296
00:24:17.616 --> 00:24:19.895
in secret.

297
00:24:22.973 --> 00:24:25.372
I might have known.

298
00:24:25.572 --> 00:24:27.372
I'll be frank with you.

299
00:24:27.572 --> 00:24:29.411
I'm a bit hot-tempered.

300
00:24:29.571 --> 00:24:32.090
Is that a fact. sir?
- One of my little character flaws.

301
00:24:32.450 --> 00:24:34.289
Well...

302
00:24:34.569 --> 00:24:36.888
I'll admit that this money is a great relief.

303
00:24:37.168 --> 00:24:40.606
Food and all the rest of it. as you well know.
are getting scarce and expensive.

304
00:24:40.806 --> 00:24:43.405
That's where Sir D'Arcy
thought I might come in handy. sir.

305
00:24:43.765 --> 00:24:47.883
I've managed to keep up some contacts.
I've got one or two... friends in the black market.

306
00:24:49.723 --> 00:24:52.122
Have a chair.
- Oh. Thank you very much. sir.

307
00:24:53.841 --> 00:24:57.000
The big problem. if there's to be
as many escapers as you expect.

308
00:24:57.200 --> 00:24:59.878
will be finding Italian civilians
willing to hide them.

309
00:25:00.278 --> 00:25:02.477
Provided you intend to carry on with the job. sir.

310
00:25:02.757 --> 00:25:05.516
That's another thing.
That's the reason I went to see your boss.

311
00:25:05.836 --> 00:25:10.234
If someone doesn't do something quick. all those
people are going to be in mortal danger.

312
00:25:10.514 --> 00:25:12.913
That's right. sir.

313
00:25:13.473 --> 00:25:15.712
Well. I've got a few friends I could call on.

314
00:25:16.072 --> 00:25:18.951
So have I.
- Meanwhile...

315
00:25:19.231 --> 00:25:22.869
you and I could start organising things.
- In what way. sir?

316
00:25:24.988 --> 00:25:27.387
Mr West...

317
00:25:28.067 --> 00:25:31.026
.. how'd you like to go into
the real estate business?

318
00:25:43.101 --> 00:25:47.059
<i>Mi piace molto. Lo prendo. Grazie. signora.</i>

319
00:26:00.094 --> 00:26:03.333
Fine. We'll take it. This is the best yet.
- Certainly the most expensive.

320
00:26:03.533 --> 00:26:05.852
And the safest.
They'd never think of looking here.

321
00:26:06.132 --> 00:26:08.811
Right. Just round the corner
from Gestapo headquarters.

322
00:26:11.689 --> 00:26:14.768
<i>What do you mean you're not going to let us in?</i>

323
00:26:15.048 --> 00:26:19.246
<i>Dove... iI ufficizio?</i>

324
00:26:20.486 --> 00:26:22.885
Isn't there someone we can talk to?

325
00:26:27.803 --> 00:26:29.802
Lieutenant Barnett. sir. Royal Tank Corps.

326
00:26:30.082 --> 00:26:33.920
Holy Mother of God. Lieutenant.
This is St Peter's Square not a parade ground.

327
00:26:34.200 --> 00:26:38.319
Sorry. sir. I understand you can help us.
- Well. I might.

328
00:26:38.639 --> 00:26:41.397
Now. we're not changing the guard
at Buckingham Palace.

329
00:26:41.797 --> 00:26:44.196
Can you just walk along behind us
like normal people?

330
00:27:19.062 --> 00:27:21.581
Try not to get used to it. lads.

331
00:27:21.741 --> 00:27:24.460
This is our safest house.
Keep it for emergencies.

332
00:27:24.620 --> 00:27:27.979
In a day or two you'll be moved
somewhere a little less elegant.

333
00:27:30.498 --> 00:27:32.577
Born in Ireland. sir. of peasant stock.

334
00:27:32.777 --> 00:27:37.015
Late entry into the Jesuit college. where
he was known for his anti-British sentiments.

335
00:27:37.375 --> 00:27:38.614
Is that so?

336
00:27:38.814 --> 00:27:42.293
Appointed Vice-Rector of Propaganda
at the college here in Rome at the age of 28.

337
00:27:42.653 --> 00:27:44.772
Then Vatican Charge d'Affaires in Egypt.

338
00:27:45.052 --> 00:27:47.531
He'd been transferred to the diplomatic service?

339
00:27:47.851 --> 00:27:50.250
Yes. sir.
- Well. well.

340
00:27:51.689 --> 00:27:53.488
A resourceful man.

341
00:27:53.768 --> 00:27:56.567
<i>What is this note - "Czechoslovakia 1 936"?</i>

342
00:27:56.767 --> 00:27:58.566
Er... I don't know. sir.

343
00:27:58.846 --> 00:28:00.765
Where did the information come from?

344
00:28:00.965 --> 00:28:04.804
Er... from Beck. sir. of the secret police.
He is outside.

345
00:28:05.084 --> 00:28:07.483
So. bring him in.

346
00:28:13.920 --> 00:28:16.799
<i>Explain this note for me -
"Czechoslovakia 1 936".</i>

347
00:28:18.878 --> 00:28:21.117
That is when O'Flaherty was sent there. sir.

348
00:28:21.397 --> 00:28:24.156
The purpose of his mission
has never been discovered.

349
00:28:24.356 --> 00:28:27.435
But in '38. when he returned to Rome
to join the Holy Office.

350
00:28:27.714 --> 00:28:30.313
several of the people
whom he was associated with.

351
00:28:30.673 --> 00:28:33.552
and whom the Gestapo wanted to interview.
disappeared.

352
00:28:33.832 --> 00:28:35.591
He helped them to escape?

353
00:28:35.751 --> 00:28:39.030
Nothing is certain -
only that he was connected with them.

354
00:28:39.310 --> 00:28:41.909
I have put him under surveillance.
as you ordered.

355
00:28:42.269 --> 00:28:45.547
<i>But my men can only follow him
once he crosses the white line.</i>

356
00:28:45.747 --> 00:28:48.226
<i>So far they have nothing of interest to report.</i>

357
00:28:48.506 --> 00:28:51.305
But I am interested. Beck. Very interested.

358
00:28:51.665 --> 00:28:54.664
<i>Keep watching him. Anything more
you can learn. I want to know at once.</i>

359
00:28:54.943 --> 00:28:57.223
At your orders. Colonel.

360
00:29:12.017 --> 00:29:16.135
Black market prices are rising. Monsignor.
almost every day. It's supply and demand.

361
00:29:16.415 --> 00:29:19.094
We'll need at least 200 lire a week
for each escaper.

362
00:29:19.374 --> 00:29:23.212
We'll have to pass the hat round again.
Mine's the largest so we'll leave that to me.

363
00:29:23.612 --> 00:29:25.531
Yes. Reverend Mother?

364
00:29:25.811 --> 00:29:28.130
Clothes. Monsignor.
We need boots and shoes.

365
00:29:28.410 --> 00:29:31.849
And many of the men are seriously ill.
They need treatment.

366
00:29:32.048 --> 00:29:34.248
Father Morosini. your department.

367
00:29:34.527 --> 00:29:36.647
The hospital of Santa Croce is in my parish.

368
00:29:36.926 --> 00:29:40.685
The pharmacist promised us
whatever medical supplies he can spare.

369
00:29:40.965 --> 00:29:43.084
First-rate. Anything else?

370
00:29:43.364 --> 00:29:44.803
<i>If I could make a suggestion. sir.</i>

371
00:29:45.083 --> 00:29:47.282
We've got a lot of men here. trained men.

372
00:29:47.562 --> 00:29:49.401
Are they just going to sit around?

373
00:29:49.681 --> 00:29:54.559
No. we can use them for sabotage
or cutting lines of communications

374
00:29:54.959 --> 00:29:57.238
<i>or setting explosives.</i>

375
00:29:57.438 --> 00:29:59.357
An army without guns?

376
00:29:59.557 --> 00:30:02.156
Half of them wounded. half starving?

377
00:30:03.396 --> 00:30:05.875
All over Rome.
partisan groups are being formed.

378
00:30:06.075 --> 00:30:08.674
Father. if that's what you want.
then join one of them.

379
00:30:08.954 --> 00:30:10.593
We're not a Resistance group.

380
00:30:10.873 --> 00:30:13.072
<i>We're not here to blow up trains.
- But...</i>

381
00:30:13.352 --> 00:30:15.471
Let me say it once and for all.

382
00:30:15.751 --> 00:30:21.109
As priests it's our duty to do all we can
to help those in danger. the victims of the war.

383
00:30:21.588 --> 00:30:23.987
We're not here to add to the killing.

384
00:30:25.347 --> 00:30:27.266
Forgive me. Monsignor.

385
00:30:27.546 --> 00:30:29.745
Now... back to business.

386
00:30:30.025 --> 00:30:35.103
Count Langenthal. you're talking about spare
rooms. well. they're getting scarcer and scarcer.

387
00:30:35.583 --> 00:30:37.622
<i>but we managed to dig up a few.
- Good.</i>

388
00:30:37.902 --> 00:30:40.661
You have no idea how many escapers
come to me at the Swiss consulate.

389
00:30:40.981 --> 00:30:42.900
but I have to be able to tell them where to go.

390
00:30:43.180 --> 00:30:44.979
Well. I've been thinking about that.

391
00:30:45.299 --> 00:30:47.498
I want you all to pass the word.

392
00:30:47.778 --> 00:30:51.496
I'll be near the steps of St Peter's.
if anyone needs me.

393
00:30:51.816 --> 00:30:54.775
every afternoon from three till five.

394
00:30:55.055 --> 00:30:58.214
That might be a bit dodgy. sir.
You'll be setting yourself up as a target.

395
00:30:58.613 --> 00:31:00.253
Oh. don't worry. my boy.

396
00:31:00.413 --> 00:31:02.732
I'll only be a target for the pigeons.

397
00:31:47.994 --> 00:31:50.393
Ah. Rabbi Leoni.

398
00:31:50.952 --> 00:31:53.071
Good afternoon. gentlemen. Buona sera.

399
00:31:53.351 --> 00:31:55.630
Relax. gentlemen. relax.

400
00:31:56.510 --> 00:31:59.869
You will have noticed how few Jews
have been bothered...

401
00:32:01.308 --> 00:32:05.227
.. and not one single piece of Jewish property
has been damaged...

402
00:32:06.386 --> 00:32:08.785
.. since the SS took control in Rome.

403
00:32:09.345 --> 00:32:11.744
You and your families are quite safe.

404
00:32:11.944 --> 00:32:16.462
Please understand. Colonel.
we have heard stories... rumours.

405
00:32:17.901 --> 00:32:20.300
Allied propaganda. I suspect.

406
00:32:20.860 --> 00:32:23.339
But I promise you
that there will be no ill-treatment.

407
00:32:23.659 --> 00:32:28.737
no deportations to forced labour
or so-called death camps.

408
00:32:31.016 --> 00:32:33.615
You can take it from me
these camps do not exist.

409
00:32:34.775 --> 00:32:38.893
You and your families will be treated
exactly the same way as any other Italian.

410
00:32:39.253 --> 00:32:42.332
Thank you. Colonel.
You have spoken frankly. so must I.

411
00:32:43.571 --> 00:32:46.170
These are words we never expected to hear.

412
00:32:46.450 --> 00:32:48.849
There is one small point. however.

413
00:32:49.609 --> 00:32:52.008
I have shown you my good faith.

414
00:32:52.607 --> 00:33:00.924
To show yours. I must ask the Jewish community
to pay an indemnity of one million lire

415
00:33:01.524 --> 00:33:05.322
and one hundred pounds in pure gold.

416
00:33:05.722 --> 00:33:09.481
<i>This must be delivered to this office
within 36 hours or...</i>

417
00:33:09.760 --> 00:33:13.879
I'm afraid I may not be able
to keep my guarantees.

418
00:33:14.239 --> 00:33:17.317
Such an amount of gold is impossible to raise
in such a short time.

419
00:33:17.717 --> 00:33:20.196
<i>ColoneI. I beg you. please give us a little longer.</i>

420
00:33:21.356 --> 00:33:23.155
I'm sorry.

421
00:33:23.475 --> 00:33:25.754
36 hours.

422
00:33:26.154 --> 00:33:28.553
Starting now.

423
00:33:31.232 --> 00:33:33.631
A hundred pounds of gold?

424
00:33:33.911 --> 00:33:36.030
The elders say we have to trust Kappler.

425
00:33:36.190 --> 00:33:39.189
They say that somehow
we must try to raise the full amount.

426
00:33:39.468 --> 00:33:42.147
This Colonel Kappler. he gave his word. did he?

427
00:33:42.427 --> 00:33:44.626
Like he told them
there are no extermination camps.

428
00:33:45.026 --> 00:33:49.624
Hold on. Simon. Just hold on.
I've got a lot of friends. They've got friends.

429
00:33:49.904 --> 00:33:53.943
<i>You tell Dr Leoni we'll all pitch in
and do what we can. Here.</i>

430
00:33:55.662 --> 00:33:59.220
It doesn't weigh much... but it's a start for you.

431
00:35:29.024 --> 00:35:30.863
Well?

432
00:35:31.063 --> 00:35:33.342
Exactly one hundred pounds. sir.

433
00:35:34.222 --> 00:35:36.621
Exactly?
- To the ounce. Colonel.

434
00:35:37.581 --> 00:35:39.980
Thank you. Doctor.

435
00:35:43.418 --> 00:35:48.416
Typical! They swore they had no gold. but they
could find it quickly enough when they had to.

436
00:35:48.776 --> 00:35:50.615
So it seems.

437
00:35:50.895 --> 00:35:54.334
And now they're going out free.
We should have asked for twice as much.

438
00:35:54.734 --> 00:35:57.133
You're too greedy. Hirsch.

439
00:35:57.413 --> 00:35:59.612
I didn't want to make it impossible for them.

440
00:35:59.892 --> 00:36:01.811
Sir?
- If we had raided their ghetto.

441
00:36:02.131 --> 00:36:05.010
how long would it have taken us
and how much would we have found?

442
00:36:05.290 --> 00:36:07.689
At best. less than half.

443
00:36:09.688 --> 00:36:12.087
Let them do our work for us.

444
00:36:15.525 --> 00:36:16.765
My arm is killing me.

445
00:36:16.965 --> 00:36:19.564
You shouldn't have got your tank
shot out from under you.

446
00:36:19.964 --> 00:36:21.683
I thought you said this was a short cut.

447
00:36:21.763 --> 00:36:24.562
So it is.
We'll cut through the old ghetto just up ahead.

448
00:36:24.842 --> 00:36:28.280
Could we slow down. just a little?
- Not on your life. Lieutenant.

449
00:36:28.560 --> 00:36:33.478
That's Regina Coeli prison. where you'll wind up
if you tangle with one of the German patrols.

450
00:36:33.958 --> 00:36:36.157
Those look like Italians on guard. Father.

451
00:36:36.437 --> 00:36:39.236
So they are. poor devils.
Working for the Gestapo now.

452
00:36:42.195 --> 00:36:46.233
We're trying to arrange for some
artistic reproductions of Vatican passes.

453
00:36:46.593 --> 00:36:48.432
Good as the real thing.

454
00:36:48.712 --> 00:36:51.471
Even with them
you're going to have to watch your step.

455
00:36:56.749 --> 00:37:00.587
<i>Quick. the both of you. split up.
Remember the address - Via Grazzini 21.</i>

456
00:37:15.461 --> 00:37:16.701
Hierher!

457
00:37:16.901 --> 00:37:19.180
Rein!

458
00:37:36.653 --> 00:37:39.332
You. If you are wise. stay out of it.

459
00:37:39.611 --> 00:37:42.970
Why are you doing this?
- We need more people in the work camps.

460
00:37:43.370 --> 00:37:45.929
<i>These have been chosen.
The chosen people.</i>

461
00:37:46.209 --> 00:37:48.608
But their security was guaranteed.

462
00:37:49.567 --> 00:37:51.407
They paid for it.

463
00:37:51.687 --> 00:37:53.806
Who gave these orders?

464
00:37:54.086 --> 00:37:56.405
Colonel Kappler. Take it up with him.

465
00:38:03.482 --> 00:38:04.921
Kappler.

466
00:38:05.201 --> 00:38:07.520
Then you make a wish...

467
00:38:09.119 --> 00:38:11.359
.. and you... you throw them in...

468
00:38:11.638 --> 00:38:13.438
Ah.
-.. and your wish will come true.

469
00:38:13.638 --> 00:38:17.476
Mamma says if you throw in a coin.
it means one day you will come back to Rome.

470
00:38:17.676 --> 00:38:20.155
That's a wish that's bound to be granted

471
00:38:20.555 --> 00:38:22.834
because we're never going to leave.

472
00:38:25.833 --> 00:38:28.232
Gregorian chant

473
00:39:06.456 --> 00:39:08.855
Baroque flute

474
00:39:14.053 --> 00:39:17.212
After all the trouble I'd taken to land on a bunker.

475
00:39:17.412 --> 00:39:20.651
the Bishop hit his ball a mighty swipe
and it disappeared.

476
00:39:21.050 --> 00:39:23.609
It wasn't on the fairway.
it wasn't in the rough.

477
00:39:23.929 --> 00:39:26.968
Where was it?
- It had ricocheted off a tree. hit the fence

478
00:39:27.288 --> 00:39:31.286
and bounced into the back of an open truck.
which took it all the way to Genoa.

479
00:39:32.526 --> 00:39:34.925
It was the longest drive in history.

480
00:39:36.364 --> 00:39:38.963
Good evening. Count Langenthal.
- Monsignor.

481
00:39:39.363 --> 00:39:42.322
I am always sure to meet you
at Prince Mateo's parties.

482
00:39:42.522 --> 00:39:46.440
I er... have another six packages
arriving tomorrow. Where can I put them?

483
00:39:46.840 --> 00:39:52.198
<i>Six more? That'd be at 63 Via Rienzi
and the apartment in Piazza Lucca.</i>

484
00:39:52.558 --> 00:39:54.877
Tres bien.

485
00:40:00.235 --> 00:40:03.393
You're socialising with the Swiss consul.
I see. Monsignor.

486
00:40:03.593 --> 00:40:06.752
One meets all the best people at your parties.
Prince Mateo.

487
00:40:07.152 --> 00:40:10.231
And at least four of them
hiding escaped prisoners.

488
00:40:11.670 --> 00:40:14.069
Don't worry. I won't say anything.

489
00:40:14.629 --> 00:40:17.787
I know you are interested in paintings
of the Roman school.

490
00:40:18.947 --> 00:40:21.346
I have one you haven't seen before.

491
00:40:21.906 --> 00:40:24.305
I'd appreciate your opinion of it. Please...

492
00:40:28.063 --> 00:40:29.863
You don't deny what I said.

493
00:40:30.142 --> 00:40:31.982
You seem very well informed.

494
00:40:32.262 --> 00:40:36.020
I have known of your work for some time
and I am ashamed to have done nothing.

495
00:40:36.180 --> 00:40:38.019
I believe you're short of money.

496
00:40:38.299 --> 00:40:40.778
That's a slight understatement. We're flat broke.

497
00:40:43.177 --> 00:40:45.776
It is risky to draw out large amounts too often.

498
00:40:47.416 --> 00:40:49.815
Here are 300.000 lire.

499
00:40:50.374 --> 00:40:52.214
I'll give you more as soon as I can.

500
00:40:52.493 --> 00:40:54.972
I want to give you... some warning.

501
00:40:55.372 --> 00:40:57.172
Warning? What about?

502
00:40:57.491 --> 00:40:59.211
Yes. I hear things.

503
00:40:59.411 --> 00:41:02.569
For instance. the Gestapo is watching you.

504
00:41:02.849 --> 00:41:06.208
Are they. now?
Well. that'll keep them out of trouble.

505
00:41:06.488 --> 00:41:08.887
Don't take it so lightly. my friend.

506
00:41:09.766 --> 00:41:13.205
Herbert Kappler
is an extremely dangerous man.

507
00:42:42.249 --> 00:42:46.767
<i>He's seen at all the most fashionable
restaurants. at all the best parties.</i>

508
00:42:47.127 --> 00:42:49.446
<i>He is as much a playboy as a priest.</i>

509
00:42:51.086 --> 00:42:53.485
Perhaps.

510
00:42:55.204 --> 00:42:57.603
Beck. have you learnt anything more?

511
00:42:58.762 --> 00:43:02.761
We heard he helped organise
a gold collection for the Jews.

512
00:43:06.119 --> 00:43:08.518
<i>Shall we pick him up?</i>

513
00:43:10.078 --> 00:43:11.597
No.

514
00:43:11.877 --> 00:43:14.836
We could always sweat a confession out of him.
Colonel.

515
00:43:15.156 --> 00:43:17.355
It's a delicate situation. Beck.

516
00:43:17.635 --> 00:43:20.993
It calls for kid gloves.
not your rubber truncheon.

517
00:43:23.113 --> 00:43:26.751
Monsignor O'Flaherty
is an important Vatican official...

518
00:43:28.071 --> 00:43:31.909
.. a protege of the Pope.
We cannot touch him without proof.

519
00:43:32.189 --> 00:43:34.308
People must help him.
does that go for them too?

520
00:43:34.588 --> 00:43:36.427
It does not!

521
00:43:36.627 --> 00:43:38.826
It's time these Italians were taught a lesson.

522
00:43:39.106 --> 00:43:41.025
I want checkpoints at every major street.

523
00:43:41.225 --> 00:43:43.984
and random checks on identity papers
throughout the city

524
00:43:44.384 --> 00:43:46.183
and a curfew starting tonight.
- Sir.

525
00:43:46.503 --> 00:43:50.422
No-one to go out after dark without permission.
anyone without a permit to be arrested

526
00:43:50.701 --> 00:43:53.980
and anyone who does not stop for questioning
to be shot on sight!

527
00:43:58.298 --> 00:44:00.098
And I want guards...

528
00:44:00.378 --> 00:44:02.697
on that white line.

529
00:44:03.936 --> 00:44:06.615
Until these people learn who their friends are...

530
00:44:09.014 --> 00:44:11.413
.. we'll bring the shutters down on Rome.

531
00:46:06.567 --> 00:46:08.926
Ah. Monsignor O'Flaherty.

532
00:46:11.724 --> 00:46:17.282
I am told that for the first time in living memory
our work at the Holy Office is nearly up to date.

533
00:46:17.762 --> 00:46:20.641
We're getting there. Your Holiness.
slowly but surely.

534
00:46:20.841 --> 00:46:23.240
Walk with me. my son.

535
00:46:24.479 --> 00:46:28.997
Our work here is never easy. but the war
has made it infinitely more complicated.

536
00:46:30.237 --> 00:46:33.196
Every day the white line
becomes more like a prison wall.

537
00:46:33.596 --> 00:46:36.754
Every day we become more aware
of all the suffering outside.

538
00:46:37.914 --> 00:46:41.632
So many calls for help.
- One does what one can. Holy Father.

539
00:46:42.872 --> 00:46:45.871
Each of my priests
must do as his conscience tells him.

540
00:46:46.990 --> 00:46:51.708
I only ask that whatever action is taken.
it does not affect Vatican neutrality.

541
00:46:51.988 --> 00:46:53.987
<i>However.</i>

542
00:46:54.307 --> 00:46:57.346
although officially
I am unaware of my priests' activities.

543
00:46:57.626 --> 00:47:02.904
it also means that there is very little that I can do
to save any of them... if they are caught.

544
00:47:22.456 --> 00:47:24.695
<i>We are going to need more food.</i>

545
00:47:24.975 --> 00:47:26.774
<i>This will mean moving about more.</i>

546
00:47:27.054 --> 00:47:29.853
<i>I was wondering
if we could use neutraI passports.</i>

547
00:47:30.053 --> 00:47:32.932
Well. we have a few Swiss and Spanish
for emergencies

548
00:47:33.291 --> 00:47:36.450
but to get more. even good forgeries.
is almost impossible.

549
00:47:36.650 --> 00:47:39.649
I think you'll have to rely on
the Vatican passes for now.

550
00:47:42.888 --> 00:47:44.887
Francesca. we were that worried about you.

551
00:47:45.087 --> 00:47:46.926
Sorry I'm late.

552
00:47:47.206 --> 00:47:48.925
German patrols stopped me twice.

553
00:47:49.045 --> 00:47:50.764
I thought I'd never get here.

554
00:47:51.044 --> 00:47:53.044
Well. we've not time to recap. I'm afraid.

555
00:47:53.323 --> 00:47:57.002
It's almost time for Kappler's unholy curfew.
Jack will fill you in later.

556
00:47:57.362 --> 00:48:04.359
We're now looking after over 1.700 escapers.
1.726 to be exact.

557
00:48:04.759 --> 00:48:06.198
<i>That means tighter security.</i>

558
00:48:06.478 --> 00:48:10.197
From now on. when we contact each other
it'll be through code names.

559
00:48:10.596 --> 00:48:12.036
Go ahead. Harry.

560
00:48:12.236 --> 00:48:16.554
Nothing elaborate. The simpler a code name.
the easier it is to remember.

561
00:48:16.834 --> 00:48:19.233
<i>and hopefully the harder for the enemy to break.</i>

562
00:48:19.593 --> 00:48:23.231
Now. Francesca... you'll be Malta.

563
00:48:23.431 --> 00:48:26.710
The Monsignor... will be Golf.

564
00:48:27.070 --> 00:48:29.389
Father Vittorio will be Vicky;

565
00:48:30.069 --> 00:48:32.548
<i>Mr West-Jeeves;</i>

566
00:48:32.827 --> 00:48:35.826
<i>Count LangenthaI - Edelweiss;</i>

567
00:48:36.106 --> 00:48:38.385
<i>Simon - Doc</i>

568
00:48:38.665 --> 00:48:41.664
<i>and Father Morosini - Boots.</i>

569
00:48:41.864 --> 00:48:44.343
I'll be Tommy
and Lieutenant Manning will be Joe.

570
00:48:44.623 --> 00:48:46.622
And what is my code name?

571
00:48:46.942 --> 00:48:50.940
We thought we'd call you Big Mamma.

572
00:48:51.340 --> 00:48:54.019
And now we're going to have to break up
before sunset.

573
00:48:54.419 --> 00:48:57.378
And we have to run and hide in our own city.

574
00:48:57.657 --> 00:49:02.735
When my parish people need a priest after dark.
I cannot even go to them.

575
00:49:03.135 --> 00:49:07.333
At the moment the Germans
are making the rules. Father.

576
00:49:07.653 --> 00:49:11.172
but we can be thinking up one or two ways
to twist them around.

577
00:49:25.846 --> 00:49:28.245
<i>.. Zimmers durchsuchen...</i>

578
00:49:34.203 --> 00:49:36.002
Albero di vero.

579
00:49:36.282 --> 00:49:38.121
E.
- E vero.

580
00:49:38.321 --> 00:49:42.039
<i>Gli alberi sono veri.</i>

581
00:49:42.239 --> 00:49:44.638
<i>Very good.</i>

582
00:49:50.316 --> 00:49:52.035
It's all right.

583
00:49:52.315 --> 00:49:53.755
I'll get it.
- No. Emilia will go.

584
00:49:53.955 --> 00:49:56.234
Yes. Mamma.

585
00:49:58.153 --> 00:50:01.791
Emilia. quickly. is your mother there?
Hurry! Hurry!

586
00:50:02.071 --> 00:50:04.790
You have little time.
A German patrol is in the next street.

587
00:50:05.070 --> 00:50:07.949
<i>You'll have to get your men out.
- Clear away the mattresses.</i>

588
00:50:08.309 --> 00:50:10.028
We'll do that. Just collect your things.

589
00:50:10.228 --> 00:50:13.387
Take them to St Monica's Convent. Via Luccini.
- Good luck. ma'am.

590
00:50:13.787 --> 00:50:15.906
Emilia. set the table.
- Come on. hurry.

591
00:50:16.186 --> 00:50:18.305
Don't be frightened. you're a brave girl.

592
00:50:18.465 --> 00:50:23.463
Help me put the mattresses on the beds. then
clear up everything you see lying around. Hurry!

593
00:50:23.863 --> 00:50:26.262
Los! Wo jede wohnen.

594
00:50:26.621 --> 00:50:28.461
Schnell! Die Treppe auf!

595
00:50:28.661 --> 00:50:30.740
Schnell! Aufmachen!

596
00:50:31.020 --> 00:50:32.779
<i>Schnell.</i>

597
00:50:33.059 --> 00:50:34.858
Quickly. quickly.

598
00:50:35.058 --> 00:50:36.897
<i>Aufmachen!</i>

599
00:50:37.177 --> 00:50:39.456
Stand aside. Search the rooms.

600
00:50:47.533 --> 00:50:49.452
<i>My daughters.</i>

601
00:50:49.732 --> 00:50:52.051
Anything?
- Nothing. sir.

602
00:50:56.050 --> 00:50:58.449
May I ask what you are looking for?

603
00:50:59.128 --> 00:51:01.927
Escaped prisoners and deserters.

604
00:51:08.604 --> 00:51:11.003
Who else lives here?

605
00:51:11.883 --> 00:51:14.282
There is only the three of us.

606
00:51:21.079 --> 00:51:23.478
Hm.

607
00:51:24.238 --> 00:51:26.637
Nebenan.

608
00:51:42.951 --> 00:51:45.350
At nine you are seeing Father Gatti.

609
00:51:45.909 --> 00:51:48.988
9:30 - you review the evidence
in the Di Stefano divorce.

610
00:51:49.268 --> 00:51:51.267
They're still battling. are they?

611
00:51:51.547 --> 00:51:54.426
Sorry. If I am interrupting...

612
00:51:54.826 --> 00:51:58.264
Oh. Vittorio. it's all right. Come on in.
We'll finish that off later.

613
00:51:58.464 --> 00:52:02.103
If Father Gatti arrives. ask him to wait. please.
Sit down. Vittorio.

614
00:52:03.342 --> 00:52:05.182
How do you get through it all?

615
00:52:05.461 --> 00:52:09.380
I once worked on a farm. It's just the same -
you start early and you stay late.

616
00:52:09.780 --> 00:52:12.459
I've been hearing some gossip. Hugh.
It's worrying.

617
00:52:12.739 --> 00:52:15.817
And if you wouldn't listen to it.
you wouldn't be worried.

618
00:52:16.097 --> 00:52:21.015
There are people here in the Vatican
who are jealous of your success.

619
00:52:21.295 --> 00:52:23.974
Ah. who'd be jealous of a monsignor?

620
00:52:24.174 --> 00:52:25.973
You have enemies. Hugh.

621
00:52:26.253 --> 00:52:29.532
At the Vatican?
Why would I have enemies here?

622
00:52:29.932 --> 00:52:35.289
They say your work for the escaped prisoners
proves you are unorthodox.

623
00:52:35.649 --> 00:52:39.288
Vittorio. I'm not going to start worrying
about politics.

624
00:52:39.688 --> 00:52:42.367
You must think about your future.
- Listen to this.

625
00:52:43.806 --> 00:52:48.124
Colonel Herbert Kappler.
born Halberstadt. Germany. Son of a doctor.

626
00:52:48.524 --> 00:52:52.163
Personally recruited into the SS
by Reinhard Heydrich.

627
00:52:52.522 --> 00:52:57.520
1 938. organised deportation of Austrian Jews
to concentration camps.

628
00:52:57.920 --> 00:53:01.279
<i>Transferred to Belgium.
where he put down an insurrection in Brussels</i>

629
00:53:01.639 --> 00:53:03.358
<i>with many reported atrocities.</i>

630
00:53:03.558 --> 00:53:09.036
Add to that. in the last six months
he's supervised the deportation of Roman Jews.

631
00:53:09.396 --> 00:53:12.874
he's organised mass round-ups of people
for slave labour

632
00:53:13.154 --> 00:53:17.272
<i>and personally ordered the torture
of hundreds of civilians.</i>

633
00:53:19.392 --> 00:53:23.230
Talk about my career.
my little enemies in the Vatican...

634
00:53:25.229 --> 00:53:27.628
.. here's the real enemy.

635
00:53:49.859 --> 00:53:51.699
Padre!
- What is it. Harry?

636
00:53:51.978 --> 00:53:55.417
There's bad news. Father Morosini
has been arrested at one of the checkpoints.

637
00:53:55.817 --> 00:53:57.616
Arrested? Why?

638
00:53:57.936 --> 00:54:01.175
He was carrying a gun. sir.
He's been taken to Gestapo headquarters.

639
00:54:01.455 --> 00:54:05.213
As well as helping us. he's been working
for the Resistance. as a courier.

640
00:54:06.533 --> 00:54:08.932
I should have known he'd do something like that.

641
00:54:09.891 --> 00:54:11.131
Where was he picked up?

642
00:54:11.451 --> 00:54:13.850
Via Alighieri. Mrs Lombardo's sector.

643
00:54:16.688 --> 00:54:18.608
You'd better warn her immediately.

644
00:54:18.928 --> 00:54:20.647
And all of our people in that area.

645
00:54:20.927 --> 00:54:23.806
Start moving as many as you can
to other sectors.

646
00:54:24.085 --> 00:54:25.525
They won't force him to talk.

647
00:54:25.805 --> 00:54:28.004
I mean. they wouldn't torture a priest.

648
00:54:28.324 --> 00:54:30.803
Get moving. Harry. Get moving.

649
00:54:41.918 --> 00:54:44.317
Hold him.

650
00:54:49.115 --> 00:54:51.514
Anything?
- Not yet.

651
00:54:58.512 --> 00:55:00.911
Remember me?

652
00:55:01.590 --> 00:55:04.269
Do you know who I am?

653
00:55:05.509 --> 00:55:07.908
I admire your courage. Father.

654
00:55:09.627 --> 00:55:14.705
But please understand you possess information
that we must have.

655
00:55:16.904 --> 00:55:18.743
I have...

656
00:55:19.023 --> 00:55:21.302
no information.

657
00:55:21.902 --> 00:55:23.821
For the good of your country...

658
00:55:24.101 --> 00:55:25.821
please...

659
00:55:26.100 --> 00:55:28.419
help me to put an end to the violence.

660
00:55:29.659 --> 00:55:31.098
You're a priest.

661
00:55:31.298 --> 00:55:33.577
Surely you want that. too?

662
00:55:34.817 --> 00:55:38.375
I have... no information.

663
00:55:40.215 --> 00:55:42.614
I won't even let you become a martyr. Father.

664
00:55:44.133 --> 00:55:45.972
I will have you taken to Regina Coeli

665
00:55:46.252 --> 00:55:48.531
to be shot by your own countrymen.

666
00:55:51.050 --> 00:55:54.409
<i>Surely you see it's pointless
to go through all this.</i>

667
00:55:55.648 --> 00:55:58.687
when all you have to do
is to give us a few names...

668
00:55:59.967 --> 00:56:02.366
.. and it's over.

669
00:56:07.324 --> 00:56:09.723
Very well.

670
00:56:14.521 --> 00:56:16.920
Get on with it.

671
00:56:28.795 --> 00:56:30.514
<i>Monsignor.</i>

672
00:56:30.714 --> 00:56:33.113
Is there any word?

673
00:56:34.073 --> 00:56:36.472
Only that Father Morosini refused...

674
00:56:37.152 --> 00:56:39.911
.. and still refuses to name anyone.

675
00:56:40.110 --> 00:56:42.310
<i>They've taken him to Regina Coeli prison.</i>

676
00:56:42.629 --> 00:56:45.668
And have you found out
what's to be done with him?

677
00:56:46.068 --> 00:56:47.867
The Holy Father broke his rule.

678
00:56:48.067 --> 00:56:51.626
and appealed to the German High Command
for a pardon.

679
00:56:52.985 --> 00:56:55.184
<i>They said they could not interfere.</i>

680
00:56:55.344 --> 00:57:00.622
The decision to execute him or not
lies with the SS Commandant.

681
00:57:01.022 --> 00:57:03.301
Kappler!

682
00:57:10.698 --> 00:57:13.097
My countrymen...

683
00:57:14.537 --> 00:57:16.936
.. I die for love of our country...

684
00:57:19.415 --> 00:57:21.254
<i>.. to which and to God.</i>

685
00:57:21.534 --> 00:57:23.853
<i>I dedicate my last thoughts.</i>

686
00:57:25.932 --> 00:57:28.331
Viva Italia.

687
00:57:31.330 --> 00:57:33.729
I forgive you.

688
00:58:03.317 --> 00:58:05.356
Firing party.

689
00:58:05.556 --> 00:58:07.915
<i>present!</i>

690
00:58:09.274 --> 00:58:11.673
<i>Aim!</i>

691
00:58:15.712 --> 00:58:18.111
<i>Fire!</i>

692
00:59:06.491 --> 00:59:08.411
Shoot him!

693
00:59:08.730 --> 00:59:11.010
He is a priest!

694
00:59:23.844 --> 00:59:29.122
Hallelujah

695
01:00:30.777 --> 01:00:32.417
And I got the loveliest blue dress.

696
01:00:32.696 --> 01:00:34.976
Sort of off the shoulders.
Not really very expensive.

697
01:00:35.295 --> 01:00:36.815
I shall wear it for New Year's Eve.

698
01:00:36.895 --> 01:00:40.253
<i>And a suit for Franz.
and a pretty little party dress for Liesel.</i>

699
01:00:40.533 --> 01:00:42.373
Mutti. can we open our presents?

700
01:00:42.652 --> 01:00:44.972
Of course. Why not?

701
01:00:45.811 --> 01:00:49.170
<i>And then we had lunch at a wonderful restaurant
at Piazza Navona.</i>

702
01:00:50.409 --> 01:00:53.688
Oh. Herbert. it's so beautiful.
We have to eat there together.

703
01:00:54.048 --> 01:00:55.887
Herbert?
- Hm?

704
01:00:56.167 --> 01:00:57.526
You're not listening.

705
01:00:57.726 --> 01:00:59.446
Of course I was.

706
01:00:59.726 --> 01:01:01.565
You look very tired.

707
01:01:01.725 --> 01:01:03.564
Is there something wrong?

708
01:01:03.844 --> 01:01:07.003
Oh. nothing special.
It's... the usual problems. that's all.

709
01:01:07.402 --> 01:01:09.402
<i>Oh. it's Italian!</i>

710
01:01:09.682 --> 01:01:11.401
I wanted a Bavarian doll! I told you!

711
01:01:11.601 --> 01:01:13.240
Look. Pappi!

712
01:01:13.520 --> 01:01:16.599
Oh. Herbert!
Don't they see enough guns everywhere?

713
01:01:16.999 --> 01:01:18.878
That's what he wanted.

714
01:01:19.198 --> 01:01:21.477
And it's good for him to get used to them.

715
01:01:22.636 --> 01:01:25.035
This world we live in.

716
01:01:27.314 --> 01:01:29.713
Happy Christmas.

717
01:02:27.810 --> 01:02:29.529
Can you believe it. gentlemen?

718
01:02:29.849 --> 01:02:32.248
<i>One week ago.
the Americans and British landed at Anzio</i>

719
01:02:32.408 --> 01:02:34.807
only 30 miles southwest of Rome.

720
01:02:35.007 --> 01:02:38.086
and not a single German
between them and the city.

721
01:02:38.446 --> 01:02:42.404
And then. for some reason.
some unfathomable reason. they didn't advance.

722
01:02:42.764 --> 01:02:45.283
And the time they wasted digging themselves in.

723
01:02:45.443 --> 01:02:48.722
was enough for us to bring up tanks and artillery.

724
01:02:48.921 --> 01:02:53.040
And now we've closed the gap
with two army corps.

725
01:02:53.440 --> 01:02:58.118
and the mortars.
and dive bombers on them night and day.

726
01:02:59.357 --> 01:03:01.956
<i>The Fuhrer must hear about this.</i>

727
01:03:05.035 --> 01:03:06.834
There you have it. gentlemen.

728
01:03:07.114 --> 01:03:09.433
<i>The Anzio beachhead has been contained.</i>

729
01:03:10.593 --> 01:03:12.992
Rome is as safe as ever.

730
01:03:15.271 --> 01:03:18.709
Even more so. General. The landing brought out
many partisans in the streets.

731
01:03:19.029 --> 01:03:21.028
so we were able to round them up.

732
01:03:21.308 --> 01:03:23.148
Very good.

733
01:03:23.348 --> 01:03:28.785
But I also hear that there are large numbers
of enemy prisoners among them. Colonel.

734
01:03:29.265 --> 01:03:31.584
That suggests that...

735
01:03:32.144 --> 01:03:34.943
.. even in Rome
there were more than we suspected.

736
01:03:35.223 --> 01:03:37.622
Many have been rounded up. sir.

737
01:03:38.781 --> 01:03:40.860
Soon I shall be in a position to arrest the others.

738
01:03:41.180 --> 01:03:42.900
I'm relieved to hear that.

739
01:03:43.180 --> 01:03:47.298
Reichsfuhrer Himmler himself has asked me
what is being done about them.

740
01:03:47.698 --> 01:03:49.497
I am fairly certain that um...

741
01:03:49.777 --> 01:03:52.656
this organisation
which is helping these prisoners...

742
01:03:53.895 --> 01:03:56.294
.. is being run by one man.

743
01:03:56.894 --> 01:03:58.014
A priest.

744
01:03:58.133 --> 01:03:59.933
Then deal with him. Deal with him quickly.

745
01:04:00.133 --> 01:04:03.211
The Reichsfuhrer doesn't deal in supposition.
he wants results.

746
01:04:22.364 --> 01:04:25.562
Well. that's the last department checked.
Come on. let's go home.

747
01:04:25.842 --> 01:04:27.642
Do we have to go right away?

748
01:04:27.961 --> 01:04:30.720
Your mother would kill me
if she knew I'd taken you with me.

749
01:04:31.120 --> 01:04:33.399
We never get a chance to be alone.

750
01:04:34.359 --> 01:04:35.718
OK.

751
01:04:35.998 --> 01:04:38.277
We'll take the long way home. Hm?

752
01:04:54.871 --> 01:04:57.549
Ah. thank you. Commander Tore. Thank you.

753
01:05:01.788 --> 01:05:04.187
Thank you for looking after our friends.

754
01:05:08.105 --> 01:05:10.504
Ah. good evening. Count.
- Monsignor.

755
01:05:12.024 --> 01:05:16.182
Are you enjoying the opera. Mrs Lombardo?
- Very much. Thank you. Count Langenthal.

756
01:05:16.542 --> 01:05:19.141
It's nice to be reminded
of what life used to be like.

757
01:05:19.501 --> 01:05:23.179
Could our friends in Trastevere possibly
entertain a few more visiting monks

758
01:05:23.339 --> 01:05:24.978
if I were to send them round tomorrow?

759
01:05:25.258 --> 01:05:27.577
Yes. I think we could manage that. Monsignor.

760
01:05:28.817 --> 01:05:31.896
Well. shall we be getting back
for another dose of Puccini?

761
01:05:41.012 --> 01:05:43.371
<i>Next.</i>

762
01:05:46.570 --> 01:05:47.689
<i>Do you work for the Vatican?</i>

763
01:05:48.009 --> 01:05:49.528
Yes. er... Civilian Records Office.

764
01:05:49.808 --> 01:05:51.808
Nationality?
- Irish.

765
01:05:52.127 --> 01:05:53.367
Passport. please.

766
01:05:53.567 --> 01:05:55.966
Uh. I don't carry it with me.
- Wait over there. please.

767
01:05:56.246 --> 01:05:59.404
I don't understand. This has never been...
- Colonel Kappler's orders.

768
01:05:59.684 --> 01:06:02.283
Vatican passes are no longer valid on their own.

769
01:06:02.563 --> 01:06:04.962
Next!

770
01:06:05.922 --> 01:06:08.321
<i>Documenti!</i>

771
01:06:10.040 --> 01:06:11.480
<i>Dai. passi.</i>

772
01:06:11.759 --> 01:06:14.079
<i>Avanti!</i>

773
01:06:17.437 --> 01:06:19.836
<i>Documenti!</i>

774
01:06:26.514 --> 01:06:28.913
Was machst du da?

775
01:06:30.272 --> 01:06:32.671
Portalo via.

776
01:06:36.030 --> 01:06:38.789
PUCCINl: La Boheme

777
01:07:19.452 --> 01:07:21.851
<i>Bravo!</i>

778
01:07:27.289 --> 01:07:29.128
<i>Bravo!</i>

779
01:07:29.408 --> 01:07:31.607
What will they do?
- Nothing till the morning.

780
01:07:31.807 --> 01:07:34.006
They'll check out his name
with the Irish embassy.

781
01:07:34.286 --> 01:07:37.365
It's a false name on the pass! They'll find out!
- Don't take on so. lass.

782
01:07:37.645 --> 01:07:40.524
We're going to think of something. Come along.

783
01:07:40.923 --> 01:07:42.243
Do you see something. darling?

784
01:07:42.443 --> 01:07:45.522
Yes. Someone I very much want to meet.

785
01:07:53.878 --> 01:07:55.797
Francesca.
- What is it?

786
01:07:55.957 --> 01:07:59.596
It's Kappler.
I've half an idea he wants a word with me.

787
01:07:59.996 --> 01:08:02.115
You and Guila run along now with the Count.

788
01:08:02.395 --> 01:08:04.714
Go straight home. mind. Off you go.

789
01:08:06.513 --> 01:08:08.352
I don't believe we've met.

790
01:08:08.632 --> 01:08:10.831
I'm sure I would have remembered. Colonel.

791
01:08:11.031 --> 01:08:14.470
My dear. this is Monsignor O'Flaherty
of the Holy Office. My wife.

792
01:08:14.670 --> 01:08:16.949
Monsignor.
- Good evening. Mrs Kappler.

793
01:08:17.149 --> 01:08:20.627
The Holy Office. Is that part of your church?
- We like to think so.

794
01:08:20.907 --> 01:08:23.786
My aide. Captain Hirsch.
- Captain.

795
01:08:23.946 --> 01:08:26.185
Well. I'm delighted to meet you at last. Colonel.

796
01:08:26.465 --> 01:08:28.184
I've heard so much about you.

797
01:08:28.464 --> 01:08:29.824
And I of you.

798
01:08:29.984 --> 01:08:31.623
Did you enjoy the opera. Monsignor?

799
01:08:31.903 --> 01:08:34.022
Enormously. Puccini's my favourite.

800
01:08:34.302 --> 01:08:36.421
Ah! So. we have something in common.

801
01:08:36.701 --> 01:08:39.780
Perhaps we can discuss it one day.
among other things.

802
01:08:40.060 --> 01:08:42.179
That would be delightful.

803
01:08:42.379 --> 01:08:45.337
I hope you will be my guest. in fact.
in the near future.

804
01:08:45.737 --> 01:08:48.696
That would depend on how long
you're going to stay in Rome.

805
01:08:49.856 --> 01:08:52.255
I intend to be here for a very long time.

806
01:08:53.974 --> 01:08:55.893
O'Flaherty? That's Irish. isn't it?

807
01:08:56.173 --> 01:08:58.372
Indeed it is. ma'am. As Irish as McGinty's goat.

808
01:08:58.652 --> 01:09:00.971
From the land of saints and scholars
and leprechauns.

809
01:09:02.770 --> 01:09:05.009
It's a very primitive country. I believe.

810
01:09:05.169 --> 01:09:08.048
I doubt. Hirsch.
if the Monsignor would agree with you.

811
01:09:08.248 --> 01:09:10.167
He will tell us it is a modern democracy now.

812
01:09:10.447 --> 01:09:16.205
And that's a fact. Colonel. With an elected prime
minister. parliament. religious freedom as well.

813
01:09:17.564 --> 01:09:19.963
It's a system I'd recommend to you.

814
01:09:22.442 --> 01:09:25.041
Well. I mustn't hold you up any longer.

815
01:09:25.321 --> 01:09:27.800
It's a rare pleasure.
We shall meet again. I promise.

816
01:09:29.440 --> 01:09:30.879
In the case we don't.

817
01:09:31.079 --> 01:09:33.958
I wonder if I might have a little memento
of this evening?

818
01:09:34.318 --> 01:09:38.436
Would it be asking too much
for you to sign my programme?

819
01:09:38.836 --> 01:09:40.475
Oh!

820
01:09:40.675 --> 01:09:42.954
Why not?

821
01:09:48.232 --> 01:09:50.031
Ah. you're kindness itself.

822
01:09:50.351 --> 01:09:54.669
It's been a great privilege to have met with you.
Mrs Kappler. Captain Hirsch.

823
01:09:58.188 --> 01:10:00.027
Very charming man. isn't he?

824
01:10:00.227 --> 01:10:01.547
Indeed.

825
01:10:01.826 --> 01:10:04.705
Too bad we didn't meet the lady he was with.
She was lovely.

826
01:10:04.905 --> 01:10:07.304
Yes. I would have liked to have met her. too.

827
01:10:08.664 --> 01:10:11.063
Find her.
- Ja.

828
01:10:13.542 --> 01:10:16.021
Malta. Tommy. Golf.

829
01:10:16.301 --> 01:10:17.460
Vicky.

830
01:10:17.660 --> 01:10:20.459
<i>Where did you get this?
- From a man we picked up last night.</i>

831
01:10:20.819 --> 01:10:23.618
What did they do with him?
- He was taken to the Regina Coeli

832
01:10:23.778 --> 01:10:25.697
until his identity could be checked.

833
01:10:26.017 --> 01:10:28.296
I've asked Beck to bring him here.

834
01:10:31.175 --> 01:10:33.094
We are the idiots. Hirsch!

835
01:10:33.374 --> 01:10:34.733
Sir?

836
01:10:35.013 --> 01:10:39.531
With all our technology. all our experts.
we expect something complicated.

837
01:10:39.891 --> 01:10:43.530
But suppose this is something
really very simple?

838
01:10:44.689 --> 01:10:46.608
So simple. in fact.

839
01:10:46.808 --> 01:10:48.608
it is actually quite clever.

840
01:10:48.927 --> 01:10:51.326
V for Via. for instance.

841
01:10:51.606 --> 01:10:53.406
A street.

842
01:10:53.606 --> 01:10:56.205
And the numbers would be house numbers.
- Yes. perhaps.

843
01:10:56.484 --> 01:10:58.684
And the second set?
- Number of escapers.

844
01:10:58.963 --> 01:10:59.923
Yes.

845
01:11:00.243 --> 01:11:02.922
Well. the man they picked up
will tell us if I'm right.

846
01:11:03.202 --> 01:11:07.400
It shouldn't be too difficult to work out on a map
exactly what areas these numbers represent.

847
01:11:07.800 --> 01:11:10.199
Yes?

848
01:11:11.358 --> 01:11:14.517
That man you wanted?
- Yes? Well. bring him in.

849
01:11:14.797 --> 01:11:17.196
He was released first thing this morning.

850
01:11:17.476 --> 01:11:19.595
<i>What do you mean released?
- From the prison.</i>

851
01:11:19.875 --> 01:11:24.273
They had an order... for his release
signed by you.

852
01:11:24.673 --> 01:11:27.272
That's ridiculous! I never signed anything!

853
01:11:27.632 --> 01:11:30.231
It looks like your signature. Colonel.

854
01:11:40.946 --> 01:11:43.345
<i>Golf.</i>

855
01:11:50.742 --> 01:11:52.182
Come on. Harry.

856
01:11:52.382 --> 01:11:54.661
Komm her!

857
01:12:41.562 --> 01:12:43.481
We're going to need more champagne.
- Ja.

858
01:12:43.761 --> 01:12:45.960
A night to celebrate. sir.
- Indeed it is. Hirsch.

859
01:12:46.240 --> 01:12:48.839
A most successful operation.
- Are you certain. Herbert?

860
01:12:49.039 --> 01:12:52.198
Inevitably. With a little persuasion.
the prisoners of war we have

861
01:12:52.478 --> 01:12:56.796
will tell us who the others are. and they in turn
will lead us to more men. other hiding places.

862
01:12:57.196 --> 01:12:59.115
And like ripples in the pond...
- Exactly.

863
01:12:59.395 --> 01:13:04.353
With great pleasure.
I shall invite Monsignor Golf to visit us.

864
01:13:06.272 --> 01:13:07.831
Well done. Herbert.

865
01:13:08.031 --> 01:13:10.790
I will send a cable at once
to Reichsfuhrer Himmler.

866
01:13:10.990 --> 01:13:12.310
Thank you. General.

867
01:13:12.629 --> 01:13:14.908
A clean sweep. gentlemen!
- Prost!

868
01:13:21.626 --> 01:13:22.865
Harry Barnett?

869
01:13:23.065 --> 01:13:26.624
Yeah. Paddy was out the window when
he heard the shots. but he's sure Harry's dead.

870
01:13:26.904 --> 01:13:30.142
<i>Now they've got his code book as well as mine.
I'll have to warn the others.</i>

871
01:13:30.542 --> 01:13:33.301
Wait a minute. Jack. You're in the Vatican.
you've got to stay here.

872
01:13:33.621 --> 01:13:36.020
Outside. you'd be a marked man.
- Forget it. Jack.

873
01:13:36.300 --> 01:13:38.219
They've already rounded up 65 of your people.

874
01:13:38.499 --> 01:13:40.978
We've got to move the rest
to the ones in Barnett's sector.

875
01:13:41.178 --> 01:13:43.097
If you save one. you've got to save them all.

876
01:13:43.377 --> 01:13:46.536
It's not possible! We've thousands
of escapers on the books at the moment.

877
01:13:46.856 --> 01:13:48.935
Plus all the Italian civilians hiding them.

878
01:13:49.215 --> 01:13:53.053
Monsignor. unless you can pull off a miracle.
this whole thing's finished.

879
01:13:53.453 --> 01:13:54.892
Oh. no.

880
01:13:55.092 --> 01:13:56.812
Kappler's won a few rounds.

881
01:13:57.091 --> 01:13:58.931
He's not yet won the fight.

882
01:13:59.211 --> 01:14:02.369
Now. we don't know when or where
the Gestapo will strike next.

883
01:14:02.649 --> 01:14:04.488
Everyone's in danger.

884
01:14:04.768 --> 01:14:06.568
What we've got to do.

885
01:14:06.887 --> 01:14:10.606
<i>is to move our people. all of them.
to safe places immediately.</i>

886
01:14:10.886 --> 01:14:12.725
That's going to be some operation.

887
01:14:13.005 --> 01:14:15.124
How do we set it up?

888
01:14:15.404 --> 01:14:17.603
Well. we can count on all our Italian friends.

889
01:14:17.883 --> 01:14:20.122
They're not going to let Kappler win out.

890
01:14:20.402 --> 01:14:22.201
Now. let's get started.

891
01:14:22.401 --> 01:14:24.240
There's a great deal to be done.

892
01:14:24.520 --> 01:14:25.760
Precious little time.

893
01:14:26.040 --> 01:14:27.679
I don't think we can do it in time. sir.

894
01:14:27.959 --> 01:14:29.878
We'll give it a try. lad. And remember.

895
01:14:30.078 --> 01:14:34.116
if we bring this off. it'll be something
you can tell to your grandchildren.

896
01:15:15.700 --> 01:15:17.339
Nothing!

897
01:15:17.619 --> 01:15:19.458
Every apartment empty!

898
01:15:19.618 --> 01:15:23.576
In some. coffeepots still hot. fires burning.
food on the table. Nothing!

899
01:15:23.856 --> 01:15:26.615
How did they all get away?

900
01:15:26.815 --> 01:15:28.654
He did it.

901
01:15:28.934 --> 01:15:31.253
That damned priest.

902
01:15:32.973 --> 01:15:35.372
Sir!

903
01:15:37.851 --> 01:15:39.010
This is the caretaker.

904
01:15:39.210 --> 01:15:40.610
<i>What can he tell us?
- Go on.</i>

905
01:15:40.929 --> 01:15:42.729
Tell him.

906
01:15:43.009 --> 01:15:44.768
It was him.

907
01:15:45.048 --> 01:15:46.847
<i>He wasn't dressed like a priest.</i>

908
01:15:47.047 --> 01:15:50.006
but this is the man who rented the apartment.

909
01:15:50.326 --> 01:15:52.125
<i>I will pick him up immediately.</i>

910
01:15:52.405 --> 01:15:54.164
I wish it was so easy.

911
01:15:54.444 --> 01:15:58.083
What do you mean. sir?
- He is still protected by the Vatican.

912
01:15:58.442 --> 01:16:00.282
I will have to go in

913
01:16:00.562 --> 01:16:02.881
and ask for him.

914
01:16:03.440 --> 01:16:05.839
Hat in hand!

915
01:16:25.391 --> 01:16:28.670
<i>We have respected Vatican territory.</i>

916
01:16:29.030 --> 01:16:31.629
but it has been violated again and again!

917
01:16:31.909 --> 01:16:35.188
Then I suggest you make your report
to your authorities. Colonel.

918
01:16:35.547 --> 01:16:37.387
I am the authority in Rome.

919
01:16:37.667 --> 01:16:41.585
And I tell you that an illegal organisation exists
which is hiding prisoners of war.

920
01:16:41.905 --> 01:16:44.264
<i>and is being directed by one of your staff.</i>

921
01:16:45.543 --> 01:16:48.422
I want to question him.
- I regret that will not be possible.

922
01:16:50.022 --> 01:16:51.861
You know who I'm talking about.

923
01:16:52.141 --> 01:16:54.260
Monsignor O'Flaherty of the Holy Office.

924
01:16:54.460 --> 01:16:56.459
He has charges to answer.

925
01:16:56.739 --> 01:16:59.818
I'm afraid I cannot give my permission.

926
01:17:01.057 --> 01:17:03.656
I ask only out of courtesy.

927
01:17:06.615 --> 01:17:08.534
I intend to question him now.

928
01:17:08.814 --> 01:17:11.613
I know your methods of questioning. Colonel.

929
01:17:11.813 --> 01:17:13.532
Even of priests.

930
01:17:13.812 --> 01:17:15.531
<i>May I remind you where you are.</i>

931
01:17:15.811 --> 01:17:19.769
<i>That all my officials here
have diplomatic immunity.</i>

932
01:17:20.049 --> 01:17:22.448
There is nothing more to be said.

933
01:17:29.166 --> 01:17:32.604
If you wish to create an incident here.
Colonel Kappler...

934
01:17:33.844 --> 01:17:36.243
.. please continue.

935
01:17:58.954 --> 01:18:00.593
Kappler.

936
01:18:00.873 --> 01:18:03.192
Yes. Herr General.

937
01:18:03.752 --> 01:18:06.151
He's here? In Rome?

938
01:18:08.470 --> 01:18:10.869
Yes. Yes. of course. At once.

939
01:18:11.629 --> 01:18:14.028
Is something wrong?
- No. no. no. nothing.

940
01:18:15.627 --> 01:18:19.465
But Herbert. it's five o'clock in the morning.
Will you please tell me what's going on?

941
01:18:19.785 --> 01:18:22.144
I told you. nothing. Now. go back to sleep.

942
01:18:56.211 --> 01:18:58.969
General.
Reichsfuhrer Himmler is waiting for you.

943
01:19:00.489 --> 01:19:03.488
I won't forget you said
the whole thing was taken care of.

944
01:19:03.767 --> 01:19:05.287
Why has he come to Italy?

945
01:19:05.607 --> 01:19:09.045
Because whatever happens in Rome
is likely to affect the whole Italian campaign.

946
01:19:09.325 --> 01:19:12.684
I wish I hadn't sent that cable.
Best to let sleeping dogs lie.

947
01:19:12.964 --> 01:19:15.363
This one could bite our heads off.

948
01:19:16.242 --> 01:19:18.042
<i>At ease. gentlemen.</i>

949
01:19:18.322 --> 01:19:20.641
<i>At ease.</i>

950
01:19:22.360 --> 01:19:25.639
I am delighted to see you again. General Helm.

951
01:19:25.919 --> 01:19:27.838
It's a great honour. Reichsfuhrer.

952
01:19:28.118 --> 01:19:30.437
<i>And you. ColoneI Kappler.</i>

953
01:19:30.597 --> 01:19:32.436
I am to convey to you. General.

954
01:19:32.716 --> 01:19:35.315
the Fuhrer's personal congratulations

955
01:19:35.675 --> 01:19:40.113
on the bravery and devotion of the SS
throughout this Italian campaign.

956
01:19:40.393 --> 01:19:44.511
It is our only wish to be worthy of your trust.
Reichsfuhrer.

957
01:19:44.791 --> 01:19:47.190
You have it entirely.

958
01:19:51.588 --> 01:19:53.987
Do you find it cold in here?

959
01:19:55.267 --> 01:19:56.306
No. sir.

960
01:19:56.586 --> 01:19:58.785
<i>Damp air. I expect.</i>

961
01:19:59.065 --> 01:20:01.384
Not good for my sinuses.

962
01:20:03.703 --> 01:20:05.503
Several days ago. Colonel.

963
01:20:05.782 --> 01:20:08.781
General Helm sent a cable
informing me of your success...

964
01:20:09.901 --> 01:20:12.420
.. in rooting out all resistance groups in Rome.

965
01:20:12.700 --> 01:20:13.939
<i>Yes. sir.</i>

966
01:20:14.139 --> 01:20:15.938
It was most encouraging.

967
01:20:16.258 --> 01:20:18.537
I showed it at once to the Fuhrer.

968
01:20:20.856 --> 01:20:23.895
The Fuhrer... read it?

969
01:20:24.295 --> 01:20:26.134
More than read it. my dear Colonel.

970
01:20:26.294 --> 01:20:28.413
It became the main subject of our discussion.

971
01:20:28.693 --> 01:20:32.452
It so happened...
it tied in with an important policy matter.

972
01:20:33.691 --> 01:20:37.130
Now I need to know
just how complete your success is.

973
01:20:37.410 --> 01:20:39.249
It's a very big city. sir.

974
01:20:39.529 --> 01:20:43.087
Over a million inhabitants. and there are
bound to be one or two spots of unrest.

975
01:20:43.487 --> 01:20:45.286
Quite so. Quite so. Colonel?

976
01:20:45.566 --> 01:20:48.645
The teeth of the Resistance have been drawn.
Reichsfuhrer.

977
01:20:48.925 --> 01:20:51.604
We have broken the spirit of the partisans.
- Good.

978
01:20:51.884 --> 01:20:53.723
There are no more incidents.

979
01:20:54.003 --> 01:20:55.242
Very good.

980
01:20:55.442 --> 01:20:57.761
But the report referred specifically

981
01:20:57.961 --> 01:21:00.320
to the escape organisation.

982
01:21:01.400 --> 01:21:03.799
Which you said was controlled...

983
01:21:04.479 --> 01:21:06.278
.. from the Vatican.

984
01:21:06.558 --> 01:21:08.877
You do not mention that.

985
01:21:09.437 --> 01:21:12.795
Colonel Kappler has had some success there.
too. Reichsfuhrer.

986
01:21:13.195 --> 01:21:14.994
Some success?

987
01:21:15.314 --> 01:21:17.993
You told me it had been totally destroyed.

988
01:21:18.153 --> 01:21:20.872
Er. not entirely. sir. We closed part of it.

989
01:21:21.152 --> 01:21:23.631
In other words. the report was inaccurate.
I was misled.

990
01:21:23.911 --> 01:21:26.430
Not exactly. sir.
I expect to round up those escaped...

991
01:21:26.710 --> 01:21:31.228
What you are admitting...
is that Rome is still not fully under our control.

992
01:21:31.508 --> 01:21:32.747
Is that so?

993
01:21:32.827 --> 01:21:35.226
Is that it?

994
01:21:39.185 --> 01:21:40.984
I chose you to go to Rome. Colonel.

995
01:21:41.264 --> 01:21:46.462
because I knew that you would allow nothing
to stand in the way of your success. Nothing.

996
01:21:48.661 --> 01:21:50.460
Now I have to go to the Fuhrer.

997
01:21:50.780 --> 01:21:53.059
at a time when he is under great pressure...

998
01:21:53.939 --> 01:21:57.177
.. with the Americans and the British
poised across the English Channel.

999
01:21:57.457 --> 01:22:00.536
with the damnable winter
driving our forces out of Russia.

1000
01:22:00.816 --> 01:22:04.774
with our army here in Italy
preparing to fall back before it is encircled...

1001
01:22:05.054 --> 01:22:06.694
<i>I am to go to him and say</i>

1002
01:22:06.973 --> 01:22:09.253
I was misinformed.

1003
01:22:10.612 --> 01:22:13.571
That the report
on which he has made vital decisions...

1004
01:22:15.010 --> 01:22:17.409
.. was false.

1005
01:22:17.689 --> 01:22:19.608
I could break that organisation

1006
01:22:19.888 --> 01:22:23.167
in one day. Reichsfuhrer.

1007
01:22:23.367 --> 01:22:25.286
Oh. you could. could you?

1008
01:22:25.486 --> 01:22:26.526
How?

1009
01:22:26.805 --> 01:22:27.845
Tell me how.

1010
01:22:28.045 --> 01:22:29.884
The man who runs it is a priest.

1011
01:22:30.084 --> 01:22:32.483
Protected by the Vatican.

1012
01:22:34.082 --> 01:22:37.641
If you would just allow me to... go in and get him.

1013
01:22:37.921 --> 01:22:40.240
No. no. no!

1014
01:22:40.920 --> 01:22:42.839
That is one thing you will not do.

1015
01:22:43.119 --> 01:22:47.717
It would bring about a crisis affecting policies
far beyond this present situation.

1016
01:22:48.077 --> 01:22:50.476
Rome must belong to us...

1017
01:22:51.276 --> 01:22:53.635
.. so it can be used as bargaining.

1018
01:22:55.394 --> 01:22:57.793
You will not enter the Vatican...

1019
01:22:58.073 --> 01:23:00.952
.. but you will smash that organisation.

1020
01:23:01.311 --> 01:23:03.710
Do you hear me?

1021
01:23:05.550 --> 01:23:07.949
You will do it now.

1022
01:23:14.466 --> 01:23:17.425
I chose you for this job. Colonel Kappler.

1023
01:23:22.223 --> 01:23:25.302
I would not like to think I had made a mistake.

1024
01:23:29.700 --> 01:23:32.099
Tale Of Vienna Woods

1025
01:24:02.007 --> 01:24:06.205
I'd like to invite you to my party. Monsignor.
but I'm not sure I will.

1026
01:24:06.525 --> 01:24:10.164
Why is that. now?
- You flirt with all the ladies and not just with me.

1027
01:24:10.364 --> 01:24:11.683
Ah. forgive me. Contessa.

1028
01:24:11.883 --> 01:24:14.482
When a man in my profession
is surrounded by beautiful women.

1029
01:24:14.762 --> 01:24:17.161
the only safety is in numbers.

1030
01:24:21.159 --> 01:24:22.519
What in hell are you doing here?

1031
01:24:22.799 --> 01:24:25.797
Attending the enemy's parties
is the only way to learn what's going on.

1032
01:24:26.077 --> 01:24:28.556
You should have turned this invitation down.
Kappler is here.

1033
01:24:28.756 --> 01:24:29.716
I've seen him.

1034
01:24:29.916 --> 01:24:33.354
Oh. Count. there'll be a load of food supplies
delivered to the consulate tomorrow.

1035
01:24:33.634 --> 01:24:36.113
Some nuns will be around to collect it
in the afternoon.

1036
01:24:36.513 --> 01:24:38.912
Hugh.

1037
01:24:43.590 --> 01:24:45.989
Colonel Kappler! What a surprise.

1038
01:24:46.189 --> 01:24:48.588
Not for me. Monsignor.

1039
01:24:49.188 --> 01:24:51.107
I was looking forward to continuing our talk.

1040
01:24:51.387 --> 01:24:55.026
Were you. now? I would have thought we'd
covered just about everything there was to say.

1041
01:24:55.385 --> 01:24:59.224
Ah. but that was before
I'd given you my... autograph.

1042
01:25:00.463 --> 01:25:03.062
Before I'd heard of your reputation
for being so amusing.

1043
01:25:03.342 --> 01:25:05.741
<i>You also have quite a reputation.
- True.</i>

1044
01:25:06.061 --> 01:25:08.740
But I am German. and know my enemies.

1045
01:25:09.100 --> 01:25:10.939
You are Irish.

1046
01:25:11.219 --> 01:25:14.658
How strange to feel such concern
for the enemies of your country.

1047
01:25:14.977 --> 01:25:16.297
Speaking of your enemies.

1048
01:25:16.577 --> 01:25:19.096
that's just about the entire civilised world. isn't it?

1049
01:25:19.376 --> 01:25:21.975
I was told you had wit.
I find you disappointingly obvious.

1050
01:25:22.135 --> 01:25:25.893
Well. forgive me. I just wanted to make sure
that you understood my meaning.

1051
01:25:28.652 --> 01:25:31.051
Do not attempt to provoke me.

1052
01:25:32.690 --> 01:25:35.089
I had you invited here to give you a warning.

1053
01:25:36.049 --> 01:25:40.367
After tonight. if you take one step
outside the Vatican territory.

1054
01:25:40.847 --> 01:25:42.166
you'll be arrested on sight.

1055
01:25:42.366 --> 01:25:46.805
Colonel. do I get the feeling
that you'd like to put a crimp in my social life?

1056
01:25:47.084 --> 01:25:50.043
Damn you and your social life!

1057
01:25:50.323 --> 01:25:54.362
You stay behind that white line. or you'll spend
the rest of the war in Regina Coeli prison.

1058
01:25:54.761 --> 01:25:57.120
The way the war is going.
that might not be long at all.

1059
01:25:57.440 --> 01:25:59.519
<i>You listen to me. priest.
- No. you listen to me!</i>

1060
01:25:59.839 --> 01:26:01.279
I'm from a neutral country.

1061
01:26:01.439 --> 01:26:03.198
I have diplomatic immunity.

1062
01:26:03.478 --> 01:26:06.237
I am a member of the Holy Office
of the Catholic Church.

1063
01:26:07.396 --> 01:26:09.795
You cannot tell me what to do.

1064
01:26:11.235 --> 01:26:14.593
I... own... Rome.

1065
01:26:16.313 --> 01:26:18.152
Not you.

1066
01:26:18.432 --> 01:26:20.231
not the Pope.

1067
01:26:20.511 --> 01:26:22.910
Just because you wear a frock.
it won't protect you.

1068
01:26:23.230 --> 01:26:25.029
Remember your gun-runner priest?

1069
01:26:25.309 --> 01:26:26.868
<i>I do remember him.</i>

1070
01:26:27.148 --> 01:26:31.826
And so does every person in Italy
who understands the meaning of freedom.

1071
01:26:38.264 --> 01:26:40.663
Get out.

1072
01:26:41.143 --> 01:26:43.542
Get out!

1073
01:26:45.341 --> 01:26:48.060
<i>Go back to the Vatican where you belong.</i>

1074
01:26:49.299 --> 01:26:51.698
This is your last party.

1075
01:27:32.122 --> 01:27:34.721
This is something I wanted you to see.
Monsignor.

1076
01:27:39.239 --> 01:27:41.638
The glories of the Vatican palace...

1077
01:27:42.398 --> 01:27:44.797
.. that I used to love so much when I was a boy...

1078
01:27:45.836 --> 01:27:47.676
.. now packed away down here.

1079
01:27:47.876 --> 01:27:51.594
Irreplaceable treasures - Leonardo. Raphael.

1080
01:27:51.874 --> 01:27:57.152
and relics - infinitely more precious -
of Saint Francis. of Saint Catherine of Siena.

1081
01:27:57.632 --> 01:27:59.951
the records and archives. letters.

1082
01:28:00.151 --> 01:28:02.830
from Saint Augustine. Martin Luther.

1083
01:28:03.109 --> 01:28:07.628
even from Henry Vlll of England
to the Holy Office seeking for a divorce.

1084
01:28:07.988 --> 01:28:10.507
Nearly two thousand years of history.

1085
01:28:10.786 --> 01:28:12.586
It staggers the mind. Holy Father.

1086
01:28:12.866 --> 01:28:15.105
And here it is now. buried beneath the ground

1087
01:28:15.385 --> 01:28:18.623
behind steel doors
from the threats of shells and bombs.

1088
01:28:20.542 --> 01:28:22.941
Protected from man's inhumanity.

1089
01:28:25.740 --> 01:28:28.139
Our past is full of bloodshed. Monsignor.

1090
01:28:29.179 --> 01:28:31.018
Armies have trampled us.

1091
01:28:31.298 --> 01:28:33.097
yet nothing has changed.

1092
01:28:33.297 --> 01:28:36.656
Conquerors may come and go.
but the eternal Church must remain.

1093
01:28:37.895 --> 01:28:40.294
And so it will. Your Holiness.

1094
01:28:40.974 --> 01:28:45.652
I have inherited the responsibility of
all the popes. right back to Saint Peter himself.

1095
01:28:46.052 --> 01:28:47.971
My greatest single duty

1096
01:28:48.051 --> 01:28:50.770
is to preserve the continuity of the centuries...

1097
01:28:52.570 --> 01:28:55.368
the heritage and existence of the Holy Church.

1098
01:28:56.608 --> 01:28:59.007
I have been condemned by many...

1099
01:29:00.246 --> 01:29:02.645
<i>.. for not speaking out against Nazism.</i>

1100
01:29:03.405 --> 01:29:05.804
For making a concordat with Hitler...

1101
01:29:06.364 --> 01:29:08.763
.. which guaranteed the life of the Church
in Germany.

1102
01:29:09.163 --> 01:29:11.562
Was I wrong?

1103
01:29:12.322 --> 01:29:15.880
It may not have seemed so at that time.
Holy Father.

1104
01:29:17.120 --> 01:29:19.599
Well. perhaps I could have done more.

1105
01:29:23.837 --> 01:29:28.315
The white line is a very precarious boundary
for us now. It's impossible to defend it.

1106
01:29:28.635 --> 01:29:31.674
I was surprised to see
the Palatine Guards carrying arms.

1107
01:29:31.954 --> 01:29:33.593
Only a token.

1108
01:29:33.873 --> 01:29:36.592
I have learned that Hitler
has drawn up plans to invade us.

1109
01:29:36.952 --> 01:29:40.390
and to create a puppet papacy in Liechtenstein
under his control.

1110
01:29:40.710 --> 01:29:42.989
Surely you don't think he'd go as far as that?

1111
01:29:43.189 --> 01:29:45.028
That depends on many factors -

1112
01:29:45.308 --> 01:29:47.107
on the progress of the war.

1113
01:29:47.307 --> 01:29:49.706
on the result of secret negotiations...

1114
01:29:50.586 --> 01:29:54.984
.. on how great a danger the Vatican seems
to the military authorities here in Rome.

1115
01:29:55.344 --> 01:29:57.183
I understand the difficulties.

1116
01:29:57.383 --> 01:29:58.903
I'm glad you do.

1117
01:29:59.183 --> 01:30:04.181
<i>I'm glad you realise that any activities which
give the Nazis an excuse to invade our territory</i>

1118
01:30:04.580 --> 01:30:06.580
must be avoided at all costs.

1119
01:30:06.660 --> 01:30:09.059
<i>All such activities must cease.</i>

1120
01:30:11.937 --> 01:30:15.576
The essence of statesmanship
is compromise. Monsignor.

1121
01:30:16.656 --> 01:30:18.935
I'm not a statesman. Your Holiness.

1122
01:30:19.214 --> 01:30:21.614
The questions I ask are more simple.

1123
01:30:21.933 --> 01:30:25.652
I look at things and try to understand them
in simpler ways.

1124
01:30:26.052 --> 01:30:28.531
Yes. What question
are you asking yourself now?

1125
01:30:28.731 --> 01:30:31.130
The only one that seems to matter. Holy Father.

1126
01:30:31.410 --> 01:30:34.968
What is our duty
when we come face to face with evil?

1127
01:30:35.328 --> 01:30:36.767
We must fight it.

1128
01:30:36.967 --> 01:30:38.807
If we must fight.

1129
01:30:38.967 --> 01:30:40.726
how can we compromise with it?

1130
01:30:41.006 --> 01:30:42.925
In the abstract. we cannot.

1131
01:30:43.205 --> 01:30:49.242
In practical terms. it is sometimes necessary
to proceed slowly and with caution.

1132
01:30:49.722 --> 01:30:53.441
But isn't that the same as saying
it depends on the circumstances?

1133
01:30:55.080 --> 01:30:56.919
When I was an altar boy.

1134
01:30:57.199 --> 01:31:01.397
the old priest who taught us used to say.
"Do what is right. come hell or high water.

1135
01:31:01.797 --> 01:31:03.717
and God will give you the upper hand. "

1136
01:31:03.996 --> 01:31:05.716
Sancta simplicitas.

1137
01:31:06.036 --> 01:31:08.595
For some it is easier than others.

1138
01:31:09.834 --> 01:31:11.753
Is it ever right

1139
01:31:11.953 --> 01:31:14.352
to see innocent people in mortal danger...

1140
01:31:15.112 --> 01:31:17.511
.. and turn your back on them?

1141
01:31:18.950 --> 01:31:21.269
<i>Holy Father. at this very moment</i>

1142
01:31:21.549 --> 01:31:26.907
I'm responsible for the safety of over 4.000
people hidden in Rome and outside the city.

1143
01:31:28.546 --> 01:31:30.945
So many?

1144
01:31:35.744 --> 01:31:38.143
I have spoken to you from the heart. my son.

1145
01:31:39.262 --> 01:31:41.661
You must do what you believe best.

1146
01:31:41.981 --> 01:31:44.380
<i>Think of what I have said.</i>

1147
01:31:44.940 --> 01:31:47.339
<i>God guide your decision.</i>

1148
01:32:27.323 --> 01:32:29.722
So many are depending on me.

1149
01:32:32.121 --> 01:32:34.520
Or is that the sin of pride?

1150
01:32:35.559 --> 01:32:37.359
What should I do?

1151
01:32:37.679 --> 01:32:40.078
If my life could help you. my friend.

1152
01:32:40.357 --> 01:32:42.637
I would give it.

1153
01:32:43.396 --> 01:32:45.515
I can give you the blessing of the Church.

1154
01:32:45.795 --> 01:32:47.635
but...

1155
01:32:47.914 --> 01:32:50.233
only you can decide.

1156
01:34:18.038 --> 01:34:19.557
Thank you. Prince Mateo.

1157
01:34:19.757 --> 01:34:22.156
There is more I can do to help.

1158
01:34:23.116 --> 01:34:26.674
Do you have time for some tea?
- That's the one thing I can't resist.

1159
01:34:27.034 --> 01:34:29.353
Only a moment. though.
If I don't get back soon.

1160
01:34:29.633 --> 01:34:33.272
my friends will be as nervous as long-tailed cats
in a room full of rocking chairs.

1161
01:34:39.989 --> 01:34:41.828
The emperors of Rome.

1162
01:34:41.988 --> 01:34:43.708
Masters of the world.

1163
01:34:44.027 --> 01:34:45.827
Were they like the Fuhrer. Pappi?

1164
01:34:46.107 --> 01:34:48.426
<i>A little like him. Franz.</i>

1165
01:34:49.105 --> 01:34:50.905
But with a difference.

1166
01:34:51.105 --> 01:34:53.424
The Roman Empire did not survive.

1167
01:34:54.263 --> 01:34:56.662
The Reich will last for a thousand years.

1168
01:34:57.542 --> 01:34:58.981
Yes. Pappi.

1169
01:34:59.261 --> 01:35:02.820
One day. you may take my place. huh?

1170
01:35:03.180 --> 01:35:05.019
And then. in time.

1171
01:35:05.299 --> 01:35:07.578
your sons will grow up and carry on the work.

1172
01:35:14.615 --> 01:35:18.054
It's definite.
The Germans are pulling back in the south.

1173
01:35:18.334 --> 01:35:20.653
They can no longer hold their defence lines.

1174
01:35:20.813 --> 01:35:24.571
If they're true to form. though.
they'll not give up without a hell of a fight.

1175
01:35:24.931 --> 01:35:27.250
Still. it's good to hear.

1176
01:35:27.450 --> 01:35:29.249
Thank you again. Prince.

1177
01:35:29.569 --> 01:35:31.848
I wish I could do more. Hugh.

1178
01:35:32.528 --> 01:35:34.927
Like many others. I would like to...

1179
01:35:47.962 --> 01:35:50.361
The Gestapo! Quickly!

1180
01:35:50.561 --> 01:35:52.480
Leutnant. take some men and cover the exits.

1181
01:35:52.760 --> 01:35:55.039
The rest of you. up those stairs and spread out!

1182
01:35:56.958 --> 01:35:59.637
Remember. I want him alive.

1183
01:35:59.957 --> 01:36:02.356
This door leads to the kitchen.

1184
01:36:03.195 --> 01:36:04.635
Hide in one of the storerooms.

1185
01:36:04.835 --> 01:36:06.634
I'll try to hold them as long as I can.

1186
01:36:06.954 --> 01:36:09.233
Good luck.

1187
01:36:09.913 --> 01:36:11.712
What is the meaning of this?

1188
01:36:12.032 --> 01:36:14.311
Do you know who I am?

1189
01:36:14.791 --> 01:36:17.110
It's an outrage! I shall speak to your superiors!

1190
01:36:17.390 --> 01:36:20.069
Where is he? Where is O'Flaherty?
- What are you talking about?

1191
01:36:20.349 --> 01:36:23.507
He was seen here. He's with you.
- What a ridiculous accusation. Colonel.

1192
01:36:23.827 --> 01:36:27.066
<i>Quite obviously he is not here.
- Spread out! Search every room!</i>

1193
01:37:06.490 --> 01:37:08.369
Finish your work.

1194
01:37:08.569 --> 01:37:10.408
Get out.

1195
01:37:10.688 --> 01:37:13.007
Druben.

1196
01:37:18.365 --> 01:37:19.884
<i>Don't look round.</i>

1197
01:37:20.164 --> 01:37:21.524
<i>Don't even move.</i>

1198
01:37:21.804 --> 01:37:22.963
Who are you?

1199
01:37:23.163 --> 01:37:26.122
A priest. It's me the Gestapo are after.

1200
01:37:26.522 --> 01:37:28.441
What do you want me to do?

1201
01:37:28.721 --> 01:37:31.000
Just climb down here.

1202
01:37:38.957 --> 01:37:41.356
Well. what do you think?

1203
01:37:41.636 --> 01:37:44.035
What happens to me if they recognise you?

1204
01:37:46.074 --> 01:37:47.393
You'd better hit me. Father.

1205
01:37:47.673 --> 01:37:49.912
Holy Mother!

1206
01:37:50.192 --> 01:37:52.471
Are you sure?
- Right here.

1207
01:37:53.271 --> 01:37:55.630
God bless you.

1208
01:38:16.542 --> 01:38:18.381
Hey. coalman!

1209
01:38:18.661 --> 01:38:20.180
Yup.

1210
01:38:20.380 --> 01:38:22.219
That's enough work. Get out of here.

1211
01:38:22.499 --> 01:38:24.778
Ja.

1212
01:39:00.564 --> 01:39:02.963
You're a dead man. priest.

1213
01:42:35.957 --> 01:42:38.556
It was sheer luck they missed. You know that.

1214
01:42:38.916 --> 01:42:40.755
Keep telling him that. Francesca.

1215
01:42:41.035 --> 01:42:42.874
But I can't stay cooped up in here.

1216
01:42:42.954 --> 01:42:45.153
Don't you understand?
They are going to kill you.

1217
01:42:45.353 --> 01:42:46.792
Come in!

1218
01:42:47.072 --> 01:42:48.792
Ah. Sister Candida.

1219
01:42:49.111 --> 01:42:50.911
Come on in. Ah. you're an angel.

1220
01:42:51.191 --> 01:42:53.790
You're an angel.
Thank you. my dear. Thank you.

1221
01:42:55.509 --> 01:42:57.428
You've done enough. Hugh.

1222
01:42:57.628 --> 01:42:59.067
It's not so urgent now.

1223
01:42:59.267 --> 01:43:01.546
The Allies will be here in a few weeks.

1224
01:43:02.986 --> 01:43:04.905
Hey. are you listening?

1225
01:43:05.185 --> 01:43:07.504
What on earth are you doing?

1226
01:43:27.816 --> 01:43:29.655
Buongiorno. Capitano.

1227
01:43:29.935 --> 01:43:33.014
How about a special portrait
of His Holiness the Pope. huh?

1228
01:43:33.174 --> 01:43:35.893
Go away.
- It is blessed by the Holy Father himself.

1229
01:43:36.172 --> 01:43:37.972
No? No.

1230
01:43:38.252 --> 01:43:40.651
How about a medallion of Saint Christopher?
Huh?

1231
01:43:40.970 --> 01:43:43.369
Sehr billig. Very cheap.

1232
01:43:43.729 --> 01:43:46.048
I told you to leave me alone! Get out of here!

1233
01:44:18.915 --> 01:44:20.834
Good morning. Guila.

1234
01:44:21.034 --> 01:44:23.153
Monsignor!
- Don't go bobbing at me. now.

1235
01:44:23.433 --> 01:44:27.152
Now. tell your mother to expect
three more boarders just for two nights.

1236
01:44:27.552 --> 01:44:29.671
Oh. and Jack sends his love.

1237
01:44:29.951 --> 01:44:32.070
<i>How is he?
- He's going crazy in the Vatican.</i>

1238
01:44:32.350 --> 01:44:34.269
I don't think he's cut out to be a priest.

1239
01:44:34.549 --> 01:44:35.708
But he's fine.

1240
01:44:35.788 --> 01:44:38.467
Goodbye for now.
I'm getting behind in my sweeping.

1241
01:45:45.880 --> 01:45:48.159
<i>He has been reported all over the city. sir.</i>

1242
01:45:48.559 --> 01:45:50.278
Dressed as a dustman. a coalman.

1243
01:45:50.478 --> 01:45:52.957
an ambulance driver. a mailman.

1244
01:45:53.357 --> 01:45:56.316
The Angel Gabriel. no doubt.
People will swallow any nonsense.

1245
01:45:56.596 --> 01:45:59.115
Even the ridiculous story
that he dressed up as a nun.

1246
01:45:59.275 --> 01:46:01.394
People will believe anything about him.

1247
01:46:01.674 --> 01:46:03.113
He must be stopped.

1248
01:46:03.393 --> 01:46:05.712
We have tried everything. sir.

1249
01:46:05.912 --> 01:46:08.311
No.

1250
01:46:08.871 --> 01:46:11.270
Not quite everything.

1251
01:47:05.648 --> 01:47:09.566
Well. it's not that I'm not glad to see you. Alfred...

1252
01:47:10.806 --> 01:47:13.005
.. but where in the holy name
did you come from?

1253
01:47:13.205 --> 01:47:16.843
Well. seeing as they didn't get you outside.
it was a safe bet they'd come in after you.

1254
01:47:17.243 --> 01:47:18.962
So I've been watching your back.

1255
01:47:19.242 --> 01:47:21.561
God bless you.

1256
01:47:54.508 --> 01:47:56.907
Bang! Bang! You're dead. Pappi!

1257
01:47:57.307 --> 01:47:59.306
You never do that again! Do you hear me?

1258
01:47:59.586 --> 01:48:00.865
Never!

1259
01:48:01.025 --> 01:48:02.865
Herbert! What...?

1260
01:48:03.145 --> 01:48:05.943
You poor darling. It's all right. it's all right.

1261
01:48:06.223 --> 01:48:08.342
Did you hit him?

1262
01:48:08.622 --> 01:48:10.821
You've never touched the children.

1263
01:48:11.101 --> 01:48:14.180
You've never raised your voice at them
in all their lives.

1264
01:48:49.086 --> 01:48:51.765
Be a good girl. I'll be seeing you later.

1265
01:48:52.045 --> 01:48:54.324
Goodbye. Sister.

1266
01:49:13.996 --> 01:49:15.795
Hugh.
- Yes.

1267
01:49:16.115 --> 01:49:17.634
Alfred told me.

1268
01:49:17.914 --> 01:49:21.753
Thank God you're safe.
- Don't you go thinking I'm that easy to get rid of.

1269
01:49:22.033 --> 01:49:24.432
Please. don't joke.

1270
01:49:25.311 --> 01:49:27.111
You haven't heard?

1271
01:49:27.430 --> 01:49:29.710
Heard what?

1272
01:49:30.869 --> 01:49:32.668
Father Vittorio.

1273
01:49:32.988 --> 01:49:36.427
Kappler has him at Gestapo headquarters.
- No. no.

1274
01:49:36.627 --> 01:49:39.306
No. no. He left Rome three days ago.

1275
01:49:39.666 --> 01:49:41.705
to visit our billets in the country.

1276
01:49:41.905 --> 01:49:44.384
He never got there. The SS stopped him.

1277
01:49:45.623 --> 01:49:47.462
They found money.

1278
01:49:47.742 --> 01:49:49.542
They think he's a British spy.

1279
01:49:49.861 --> 01:49:53.100
He's being interrogated at Regina Coeli.
but has told them nothing.

1280
01:49:53.380 --> 01:49:57.218
<i>He's being moved tomorrow
to a concentration camp in Germany.</i>

1281
01:49:57.498 --> 01:49:59.897
Oh. my God.

1282
01:50:01.817 --> 01:50:04.136
I've got to go to him. Right away.

1283
01:50:04.415 --> 01:50:06.135
You know that's impossible.

1284
01:50:06.415 --> 01:50:08.814
You might as well give yourself up.

1285
01:50:10.533 --> 01:50:13.612
I'm going to hear his confession
and give him absolution.

1286
01:50:14.851 --> 01:50:17.250
Nothing on God's earth will stop me.

1287
01:51:36.458 --> 01:51:38.857
Leave us. Leutnant.

1288
01:51:52.172 --> 01:51:54.931
What have they done to you. my friend?

1289
01:51:56.290 --> 01:51:58.689
It's really you?

1290
01:52:00.129 --> 01:52:01.568
Here.

1291
01:52:01.848 --> 01:52:03.687
It's holy water.

1292
01:52:03.967 --> 01:52:06.246
but all the better for that.

1293
01:52:12.484 --> 01:52:14.323
Too dangerous.

1294
01:52:14.523 --> 01:52:16.602
You should not have come.

1295
01:52:17.002 --> 01:52:19.281
Oh. I had to. my dear friend.

1296
01:52:22.280 --> 01:52:24.679
We shall not meet again. I think.

1297
01:52:28.397 --> 01:52:31.956
I came... to give you absolution.

1298
01:52:33.595 --> 01:52:35.874
Thank you.

1299
01:52:36.074 --> 01:52:38.753
I have already made confession to God.

1300
01:52:40.312 --> 01:52:43.831
<i>I heard something when they tortured me.</i>

1301
01:52:46.830 --> 01:52:51.428
You must not go again to Francesca's.

1302
01:52:52.947 --> 01:52:54.787
Why not?

1303
01:52:55.067 --> 01:52:57.346
<i>Her apartment is being watched...</i>

1304
01:52:58.705 --> 01:53:01.184
<i>.. in case you go there.</i>

1305
01:53:01.464 --> 01:53:03.863
You're sure. Vittorio?

1306
01:53:05.222 --> 01:53:07.222
Kappler...

1307
01:53:07.502 --> 01:53:10.100
could not make me talk.

1308
01:53:10.500 --> 01:53:12.779
but he talked...

1309
01:53:13.379 --> 01:53:17.018
.. as if I... I was already dead.

1310
01:53:17.378 --> 01:53:21.616
<i>He will have her arrested any time now.</i>

1311
01:53:32.331 --> 01:53:34.091
Here.

1312
01:53:34.371 --> 01:53:36.650
This is for you.

1313
01:53:38.089 --> 01:53:41.448
Please... take it with you.

1314
01:53:48.165 --> 01:53:50.084
Hail Mary.

1315
01:53:50.364 --> 01:53:52.483
full of grace.

1316
01:53:52.683 --> 01:53:53.923
the Lord is with thee.

1317
01:53:54.203 --> 01:53:56.682
<i>Blessed art thou among women.</i>

1318
01:53:56.882 --> 01:54:00.240
<i>And blessed is the fruit of thy womb. Jesus.</i>

1319
01:54:00.440 --> 01:54:02.719
Holy Mary.

1320
01:54:03.039 --> 01:54:04.638
Mother of God.

1321
01:54:04.958 --> 01:54:08.117
pray for us sinners now
and at the hour of our death.

1322
01:54:09.357 --> 01:54:11.756
Amen.

1323
01:54:34.067 --> 01:54:37.905
Guila. you take Tate and the others
to San Giovanni Maggiore.

1324
01:54:38.305 --> 01:54:39.944
Tell them that I sent you.

1325
01:54:40.144 --> 01:54:43.783
This building's being watched. so use
the cellar door and go out through the garden.

1326
01:54:44.142 --> 01:54:45.982
You got friends you can stay with?
- Yes.

1327
01:54:46.262 --> 01:54:47.901
Go to them as soon as the others are clear.

1328
01:54:48.181 --> 01:54:50.660
Don't take anything but your purse.
- Yes. Monsignor.

1329
01:54:52.859 --> 01:54:54.298
I'm not leaving Emilia with anyone.

1330
01:54:54.618 --> 01:54:57.657
She's going with us.
I'm going to get you safely out of Rome.

1331
01:54:59.296 --> 01:55:01.016
There is no doubt about it. Colonel.

1332
01:55:01.296 --> 01:55:03.335
He was in an SS uniform.

1333
01:55:03.615 --> 01:55:06.493
He was seen entering the woman's apartment.
It must have been him.

1334
01:55:06.773 --> 01:55:08.493
By the time the alert was put out.

1335
01:55:08.772 --> 01:55:11.371
he had left the city and driven through the gates.

1336
01:55:11.651 --> 01:55:15.290
I want every approach to the Vatican sealed off.

1337
01:55:17.529 --> 01:55:19.928
Put out his description.

1338
01:55:20.568 --> 01:55:24.206
I want every available man in the streets.

1339
01:55:27.285 --> 01:55:29.684
And get him.

1340
01:55:34.682 --> 01:55:37.081
Get him.

1341
01:55:41.759 --> 01:55:44.278
Allies will be here in a week or so.

1342
01:55:44.438 --> 01:55:47.517
Germans will be driven out of Rome
and you can return.

1343
01:55:47.797 --> 01:55:50.196
Stay with us.

1344
01:55:50.476 --> 01:55:54.114
There's nothing I'd want more. Francesca.
than to stay here. but...

1345
01:55:55.394 --> 01:55:56.633
.. I can't.

1346
01:55:56.913 --> 01:56:00.072
If the Germans break our escape line.
I have to be there to do what I can.

1347
01:56:00.352 --> 01:56:04.470
I have a terrible feeling
that I might never see you again.

1348
01:56:04.870 --> 01:56:07.469
I told you. I'm not that easy to get rid of.

1349
01:56:07.669 --> 01:56:10.028
Please. Hugh. don't go.

1350
01:56:11.667 --> 01:56:14.066
I'm sorry.

1351
01:56:14.946 --> 01:56:18.184
You've given so much of your strength to others.

1352
01:56:18.584 --> 01:56:20.304
I don't want to take what's left of it.

1353
01:56:20.504 --> 01:56:23.462
Oh. I'm just stubborn.
You're the one who's strong.

1354
01:56:23.662 --> 01:56:25.941
I thought I was.

1355
01:56:26.261 --> 01:56:29.140
I thought there was a good God looking after us

1356
01:56:29.500 --> 01:56:31.819
who would make sure
everything turned out all right.

1357
01:56:32.099 --> 01:56:34.098
And he will do.

1358
01:56:34.298 --> 01:56:36.137
I'll try to believe that.

1359
01:56:36.417 --> 01:56:38.696
Of course you will.

1360
01:57:16.761 --> 01:57:19.919
<i>So. after months of stalemate.
our forces are on the move again.</i>

1361
01:57:20.239 --> 01:57:23.398
<i>US and British divisions
under the command of GeneraI Mark Clark</i>

1362
01:57:23.558 --> 01:57:27.516
<i>have broken out of the Anzio beachhead and
are attacking the Nazi stronghold of Cisterna.</i>

1363
01:57:27.876 --> 01:57:30.755
<i>driving the enemy to the hills
where they are pounded day and night</i>

1364
01:57:30.955 --> 01:57:32.594
<i>by our tanks and dive bombers.</i>

1365
01:57:32.874 --> 01:57:35.473
<i>The Canadians
have broken through the Hitler Line.</i>

1366
01:57:35.753 --> 01:57:38.832
<i>and GeneraI Alexander's Eighth Army
has crossed the river.</i>

1367
01:57:39.192 --> 01:57:41.591
<i>taking 10.000 German prisoners.</i>

1368
01:57:41.871 --> 01:57:44.270
<i>The battles of Anzio and Cassino are over.</i>

1369
01:57:47.069 --> 01:57:49.747
<i>And injust a few days now.
the big one will begin.</i>

1370
01:57:51.107 --> 01:57:53.466
<i>The battle for Rome.</i>

1371
01:58:11.299 --> 01:58:13.698
Herr Major? Moment. bitte.

1372
01:58:15.617 --> 01:58:18.016
Herr Major. Moment.

1373
01:58:18.496 --> 01:58:20.895
Halt!

1374
01:58:23.574 --> 01:58:25.973
Dahinten.

1375
01:58:29.611 --> 01:58:32.010
Schnell. Schnell!

1376
01:58:32.890 --> 01:58:35.289
Nachher.

1377
01:58:44.965 --> 01:58:47.364
<i>Schnell.</i>

1378
01:58:49.003 --> 01:58:51.403
<i>Er muss in die Kirche sein.</i>

1379
02:00:05.413 --> 02:00:07.812
Herbert?

1380
02:00:09.331 --> 02:00:11.730
So late. darling. Where have you been?

1381
02:00:12.690 --> 02:00:15.089
Military headquarters.

1382
02:00:19.407 --> 02:00:21.806
Minna...

1383
02:00:26.284 --> 02:00:28.683
.. first thing in the morning. I want you to pack.

1384
02:00:29.923 --> 02:00:31.962
What?

1385
02:00:32.242 --> 02:00:33.881
In two days.

1386
02:00:34.041 --> 02:00:36.360
three at the most...

1387
02:00:37.400 --> 02:00:38.959
.. we evacuate Rome.

1388
02:00:39.239 --> 02:00:42.118
But you were ready to defend it.
You said we had weeks yet.

1389
02:00:42.398 --> 02:00:46.796
It is not to be defended. or attacked. it seems.

1390
02:00:48.235 --> 02:00:51.874
This way. Rome is saved and we save our army.

1391
02:00:54.473 --> 02:00:57.831
You'll... you'll have to give me
some crates and some boxes and...

1392
02:00:58.111 --> 02:01:00.910
There's no point.
You can only take what you need.

1393
02:01:01.190 --> 02:01:04.469
What about my things? I can't just leave them.
- You'll have to.

1394
02:01:04.829 --> 02:01:06.548
Herbert. I won't. All my things. I just...

1395
02:01:06.828 --> 02:01:09.147
Don't you understand?

1396
02:01:10.866 --> 02:01:13.265
You'll be lucky to get away.

1397
02:01:20.382 --> 02:01:22.262
I don't know what you're talking about.

1398
02:01:22.461 --> 02:01:25.060
You said there was no danger.
What about the children?

1399
02:01:25.340 --> 02:01:27.739
Listen to me. Listen.

1400
02:01:28.499 --> 02:01:30.898
Up until yesterday. there was no problem.

1401
02:01:32.058 --> 02:01:35.896
But now. it's chaos here.

1402
02:01:36.296 --> 02:01:38.575
There's no transport left.

1403
02:01:39.535 --> 02:01:41.934
I have to arrange something.

1404
02:01:43.093 --> 02:01:45.492
Will you come with us?

1405
02:01:45.852 --> 02:01:48.251
That might not be possible.

1406
02:01:49.411 --> 02:01:53.529
But you and the children must be ready.

1407
02:02:03.005 --> 02:02:05.404
Where are you going?

1408
02:02:05.884 --> 02:02:09.163
There's still something I have to do.
- What?

1409
02:02:09.522 --> 02:02:11.562
Herbert?

1410
02:02:11.842 --> 02:02:14.161
Herbert.

1411
02:02:45.668 --> 02:02:48.267
Call for help and you are dead.

1412
02:02:51.226 --> 02:02:54.024
You're going to kill me anyway.
- Not if you listen.

1413
02:02:54.304 --> 02:02:58.703
I have come here personally
with a message from Colonel Kappler.

1414
02:02:59.862 --> 02:03:01.102
He wishes to see you.

1415
02:03:01.421 --> 02:03:04.860
At Gestapo Headquarters. no doubt.

1416
02:03:05.220 --> 02:03:07.619
This is to be a private meeting.

1417
02:03:08.699 --> 02:03:10.698
Tonight. just the two of you.

1418
02:03:10.978 --> 02:03:13.297
Your safety is guaranteed.

1419
02:03:13.577 --> 02:03:15.976
Guaranteed. is it?

1420
02:03:16.655 --> 02:03:19.054
Where?

1421
02:03:19.734 --> 02:03:22.093
The Colosseum.

1422
02:04:01.397 --> 02:04:03.796
You alone?
- I am.

1423
02:04:04.396 --> 02:04:05.715
Not afraid I'll shoot you?

1424
02:04:05.915 --> 02:04:09.194
If you'd been going to kill me. your man
would already have done it in my room.

1425
02:04:09.554 --> 02:04:11.953
That is so.

1426
02:04:12.553 --> 02:04:16.191
But believe me. at this moment.
nothing would give me greater pleasure.

1427
02:04:16.551 --> 02:04:20.869
When it comes down to it. a bullet's your answer
to just about everything. isn't it?

1428
02:04:21.269 --> 02:04:22.909
The only argument you've got.

1429
02:04:23.068 --> 02:04:26.347
I know what you think of me.
you and your Church. but you forget...

1430
02:04:27.587 --> 02:04:29.306
I have my orders.

1431
02:04:29.586 --> 02:04:31.905
I am a soldier. I do my duty.

1432
02:04:32.385 --> 02:04:36.103
You can't hide behind that. Kappler.
Don't debase the word "duty".

1433
02:04:36.423 --> 02:04:39.782
My orders were to occupy Rome. control the city.

1434
02:04:40.062 --> 02:04:42.621
In a war. that means whatever it takes to do it.

1435
02:04:42.940 --> 02:04:44.180
whether you like it or not.

1436
02:04:44.460 --> 02:04:46.939
And do you think that absolves you
of any responsibility?

1437
02:04:47.139 --> 02:04:48.978
Yes.

1438
02:04:49.258 --> 02:04:51.537
What is important is the Reich.

1439
02:04:51.857 --> 02:04:54.256
Not Rome. What is Rome?

1440
02:04:55.215 --> 02:04:57.694
All its greatness is over.

1441
02:04:58.054 --> 02:05:00.373
All that's left is a picture postcard.

1442
02:05:00.653 --> 02:05:02.852
a playground for whores and priests.

1443
02:05:03.172 --> 02:05:05.731
<i>There will be a new order in Europe.</i>

1444
02:05:06.891 --> 02:05:09.850
We are evacuating Rome now.
but that means nothing.

1445
02:05:10.249 --> 02:05:11.889
We will be back.

1446
02:05:12.169 --> 02:05:15.727
The Third Reich... is the future.

1447
02:05:16.007 --> 02:05:19.646
How many murderous dictators
have talked that kind of rubbish?

1448
02:05:21.365 --> 02:05:22.804
Just look around you. Kappler.

1449
02:05:23.004 --> 02:05:26.443
You're standing where your ancient friends
entertained themselves.

1450
02:05:26.723 --> 02:05:28.842
watching lions tear the Christians to pieces.

1451
02:05:29.122 --> 02:05:31.921
but the Church is still here.

1452
02:05:32.121 --> 02:05:34.799
A lot of broken stones like these.

1453
02:05:35.159 --> 02:05:38.318
In a few years.
that's all that'll be left of your Third Reich.

1454
02:05:38.638 --> 02:05:40.157
Keep your history lesson. priest.

1455
02:05:40.437 --> 02:05:44.276
You crawl to your pope and obey his orders.
just as I obey mine.

1456
02:05:44.676 --> 02:05:47.154
You compare obedience to Hitler

1457
02:05:47.434 --> 02:05:49.753
with the faith a priest owes to his Church?

1458
02:05:50.713 --> 02:05:53.112
You think that's the same?

1459
02:05:53.592 --> 02:05:54.711
In the name of God!

1460
02:05:54.911 --> 02:05:57.230
Wait.

1461
02:05:57.710 --> 02:06:00.109
I know about you.

1462
02:06:00.389 --> 02:06:02.188
And your Church.

1463
02:06:02.508 --> 02:06:04.907
I've been... talking to people.

1464
02:06:06.147 --> 02:06:08.546
I know all about you.

1465
02:06:17.942 --> 02:06:20.341
What is it you want from me...

1466
02:06:20.621 --> 02:06:21.860
.. Kappler?

1467
02:06:22.140 --> 02:06:26.179
They say that you can't pass a beggar...

1468
02:06:27.498 --> 02:06:29.897
.. or a lame dog...

1469
02:06:31.177 --> 02:06:33.936
.. but that you see yourself
with some sort of obligation

1470
02:06:34.215 --> 02:06:37.494
to look after... anyone in trouble.

1471
02:06:37.854 --> 02:06:40.733
You help British and American prisoners.

1472
02:06:41.972 --> 02:06:45.251
Jews. Arabs. refugees. anybody.

1473
02:06:45.651 --> 02:06:49.169
It's a... part of your faith.

1474
02:06:50.729 --> 02:06:51.968
Is that right?

1475
02:06:52.248 --> 02:06:55.207
Well. I wouldn't deny it.
That's why I became a priest.

1476
02:06:55.527 --> 02:06:57.606
Brotherly love

1477
02:06:57.886 --> 02:06:59.645
and forgiveness.

1478
02:06:59.925 --> 02:07:04.323
That's... the other half of what you believe.

1479
02:07:04.723 --> 02:07:06.243
<i>True?</i>

1480
02:07:06.522 --> 02:07:07.282
True.

1481
02:07:07.602 --> 02:07:09.881
Well. I'm glad of it...

1482
02:07:10.161 --> 02:07:13.320
.. because I have three more
for your mercy wagon.

1483
02:07:13.640 --> 02:07:15.559
My wife...

1484
02:07:15.839 --> 02:07:17.758
and two children.

1485
02:07:18.038 --> 02:07:20.717
<i>If the partisans get them. they will be killed.</i>

1486
02:07:20.917 --> 02:07:23.036
I want them out of Rome

1487
02:07:23.316 --> 02:07:25.595
and safe.

1488
02:07:26.474 --> 02:07:28.873
That's what I want from you. priest.

1489
02:07:30.113 --> 02:07:33.472
You're asking me to save your family?

1490
02:07:33.751 --> 02:07:36.550
If you really believe what you preach...

1491
02:07:37.870 --> 02:07:39.029
.. you'll do it.

1492
02:07:39.109 --> 02:07:43.068
You expect me to help you
after what you've done?

1493
02:07:44.787 --> 02:07:47.186
You think you can demand forgiveness?

1494
02:07:47.746 --> 02:07:49.785
You think it comes automatically

1495
02:07:50.065 --> 02:07:51.224
<i>just because you want it?</i>

1496
02:07:51.384 --> 02:07:52.544
I'm not talking about myself.

1497
02:07:52.824 --> 02:07:56.182
You've turned this city
into a concentration camp.

1498
02:07:57.422 --> 02:07:59.821
You've tortured and butchered my friends.

1499
02:08:00.101 --> 02:08:03.100
You've violated every principle of God and man.

1500
02:08:06.658 --> 02:08:09.017
I can't believe that after all you've done.

1501
02:08:09.337 --> 02:08:10.776
you want mercy.

1502
02:08:10.936 --> 02:08:13.175
I've told you. for my family.

1503
02:08:13.455 --> 02:08:15.455
They're just part of you.

1504
02:08:15.734 --> 02:08:17.294
part of what you stand for.

1505
02:08:17.574 --> 02:08:19.573
They've taken whatever they could get

1506
02:08:19.773 --> 02:08:22.732
without a thought
for the suffering all around them.

1507
02:08:22.932 --> 02:08:26.290
And now you demand that they be saved.

1508
02:08:30.049 --> 02:08:32.408
I'll see you in hell first.

1509
02:08:34.527 --> 02:08:36.726
No.

1510
02:08:37.046 --> 02:08:38.765
You're no different from anyone else.

1511
02:08:39.045 --> 02:08:41.804
All your talk means nothing.

1512
02:08:43.163 --> 02:08:46.722
Charity. forgiveness. mercy.

1513
02:08:48.161 --> 02:08:49.881
It's all lies.

1514
02:08:50.161 --> 02:08:52.480
<i>Do you hear me?</i>

1515
02:08:53.239 --> 02:08:55.638
<i>Lies!</i>

1516
02:08:56.198 --> 02:08:58.597
Don't you talk to me about God...

1517
02:08:59.757 --> 02:09:01.876
.. and humanity.

1518
02:09:02.156 --> 02:09:04.435
I know what humanity is.

1519
02:09:05.114 --> 02:09:08.673
It's one half with the power and the will to use it.

1520
02:09:09.033 --> 02:09:11.752
and the other half only cattle to be led.

1521
02:09:14.711 --> 02:09:17.110
There's no God.

1522
02:09:17.949 --> 02:09:20.348
No humanity.

1523
02:09:21.108 --> 02:09:23.347
Do you hear me?

1524
02:09:23.627 --> 02:09:25.906
<i>Do you hear me?</i>

1525
02:09:27.465 --> 02:09:29.864
<i>Priest?</i>

1526
02:09:30.704 --> 02:09:33.103
<i>Priest!</i>

1527
02:10:20.764 --> 02:10:23.243
Everybody. just a minute.

1528
02:10:25.842 --> 02:10:28.521
Guila and I have decided
we don't want to wait any longer.

1529
02:10:28.921 --> 02:10:32.719
We want to be married.
- Oh. well done. Jack. Congratulations!

1530
02:10:33.039 --> 02:10:35.318
<i>Congratulations.</i>

1531
02:10:36.198 --> 02:10:37.837
And we want you to tie the knot. Padre.

1532
02:10:37.917 --> 02:10:40.396
It's about time. Jack.
I've had the rope ready for months.

1533
02:10:40.796 --> 02:10:43.075
If you'll pardon me. ladies and gentlemen.

1534
02:10:43.395 --> 02:10:47.593
we've all come through
and it's thanks to one man.

1535
02:10:47.993 --> 02:10:49.432
I think we ought to have a toast.

1536
02:10:49.512 --> 02:10:51.511
Monsignor O'Flaherty.

1537
02:10:51.711 --> 02:10:52.951
Thank you. my friends.

1538
02:10:53.271 --> 02:10:56.030
But if we're to have a toast.
I can think of another one.

1539
02:10:58.029 --> 02:11:00.068
To those we loved.

1540
02:11:00.348 --> 02:11:02.467
those who cannot be here with us today.

1541
02:11:02.747 --> 02:11:05.026
Hear. hear.

1542
02:11:10.624 --> 02:11:15.022
This is only the first inquiry into your activities
as Head of the Gestapo here in Rome.

1543
02:11:15.382 --> 02:11:18.461
Do you deny the systematic use of torture
on suspects?

1544
02:11:18.740 --> 02:11:21.060
Only the accepted methods of interrogation
were used.

1545
02:11:21.339 --> 02:11:24.978
That is not our information.
- I only did my duty.

1546
02:11:25.258 --> 02:11:27.657
Tell us about the pipeline.

1547
02:11:29.696 --> 02:11:33.215
Come now. Colonel. it is quite obvious
that after your forces retreated.

1548
02:11:33.415 --> 02:11:36.493
you were ordered to set up
a secret line of communication.

1549
02:11:36.853 --> 02:11:39.932
Colonel Kappler.
we know all about your wife and children.

1550
02:11:41.371 --> 02:11:42.811
Minna. isn't it?

1551
02:11:43.091 --> 02:11:45.410
<i>And Franz and Liesel?</i>

1552
02:11:47.329 --> 02:11:49.728
What do you know?

1553
02:11:50.208 --> 02:11:52.607
What has happened to them?

1554
02:11:52.887 --> 02:11:55.286
<i>Now you're playing games. ColoneI.</i>

1555
02:11:55.965 --> 02:11:58.165
<i>Your wife and children disappeared from Rome.</i>

1556
02:11:58.364 --> 02:12:01.683
<i>They were smuggled into Switzerland.
as you well know.</i>

1557
02:12:02.003 --> 02:12:04.402
<i>safe and sound.</i>

1558
02:12:06.001 --> 02:12:08.041
<i>Now. how was it done?</i>

1559
02:12:08.320 --> 02:12:10.520
<i>Who helped them?</i>

1560
02:12:10.799 --> 02:12:13.198
<i>That takes some organisation.</i>

1561
02:12:14.158 --> 02:12:16.157
<i>Now. if you tell us how it was done.</i>

1562
02:12:16.477 --> 02:12:18.196
<i>and who helped them.</i>

1563
02:12:18.476 --> 02:12:20.795
<i>it might do you some good at your triaI.</i>

1564
02:12:23.554 --> 02:12:25.953
I do not know.

1565
02:12:28.632 --> 02:12:30.551
<i>Come on. ColoneI.</i>

1566
02:12:30.831 --> 02:12:33.150
<i>Tell us. Who was it?</i>

1567
02:12:39.548 --> 02:12:41.947
I do not know.

1568
02:12:47.065 --> 02:12:49.424
Stay where you are. my son.

1569
02:12:50.503 --> 02:12:52.902
No need to rise.

1570
02:12:55.022 --> 02:12:56.421
I have only a few moments.

1571
02:12:56.621 --> 02:12:59.300
This is a great day.
I have to speak to our people.

1572
02:12:59.620 --> 02:13:02.019
But first. I wanted to speak to you.

1573
02:13:02.778 --> 02:13:06.897
In this imperfect world. you may never receive
the honour that is due to you.

1574
02:13:08.136 --> 02:13:10.615
But I wanted you to know that in my heart...

1575
02:13:11.855 --> 02:13:13.134
.. I honour you.

1576
02:13:13.414 --> 02:13:16.493
<i>I talked to you once
of the treasures of the Church.</i>

1577
02:13:17.732 --> 02:13:19.532
<i>Perhaps I deceived myself.</i>

1578
02:13:19.732 --> 02:13:23.770
The real treasures of the Church.
what makes it imperishable...

1579
02:13:25.209 --> 02:13:27.608
.. is that every once in a while

1580
02:13:27.768 --> 02:13:30.167
someone comes to it. my son...

1581
02:13:30.967 --> 02:13:33.366
.. like you.

1582
02:13:38.524 --> 02:13:40.923
May the Lord watch over you.

1583
02:13:41.305 --> 02:14:41.680
